(917, 146, 8, 'Bake in the preheated oven until almost opaque, 15 to 20 minutes; remove the baking sheet from the oven.'),
(918, 149, 1, 'Season chicken with salt and pepper.  Lightly dredge in flour.In a 5-7 qt dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat.'),
(919, 146, 9, 'Raise the oven rack with the baking sheet to the next-highest level switch the oven to broil.'),
(920, 149, 2, 'Add chicken to the dutch oven and cooke 5 minutes each side, just until browned.'),
(921, 146, 10, 'Continue cooking the fish under the broiler until the top is browned, about 10 minutes.'),
(922, 149, 3, 'Remove from dutch oven and transfer to a plate.'),
(923, 146, 11, 'Squeeze the remaining lemon half evenly over the fish.'),
(924, 149, 4, 'Add peppers, onion, and carrots to dutch oven. Cook for 2 minutes.'),
(925, 146, 12, 'Sprinkle with sesame seeds and green onions.'),
(926, 149, 5, 'Add garlic, fresh thyme, fresh oregano, and mushrooms. Cook for 1 minute.'),
(927, 149, 6, 'Add cooking white and simmer for 3 minutes.'),
(928, 149, 7, 'Add canned tomatoes, rosemary, salt, pepper, crushed red pepper, bay leaf, and thyme sprigs.  Bring to a simmer.Nestle chicken breasts into sauce and transfer to oven.'),
(929, 149, 8, 'Bake for 45 minutes or until internal chicken temp reaches 165 degrees.'),
(930, 150, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. Line a baking dish with parchment paper.'),
(931, 149, 9, 'Serve with pasta and garnish with parmesan cheese.'),
(932, 150, 2, 'Place the sweet potatoes in the baking dish, and prick each one a couple of times with a fork. Slide the sweet potatoes into the oven and bake until very tender, about 45 minutes (mine took 5 to 10 minutes extra since they were a little bigger than specified).'),
(933, 150, 3, 'In a medium saucepan, combine the basmati rice, black beans, cumin, garlic, olive oil, tomato paste and salt.'),
(934, 150, 4, 'Pour 1  cups water into the pot. Cover and bring to a boil over medium heat. Lower the heat to a simmer, and cook until all of the liquid is absorbed, about 40 minutes. Cover and set aside to keep the rice warm.'),
(935, 150, 5, 'Make the rustic salsa: In a medium bowl, combine the bell pepper, cherry tomatoes, red onions, lime juice, cilantro and olive oil. Season the mixture with salt and pepper, and toss to combine. Set aside.'),
(936, 150, 6, 'Make the guacamole: Peel the avocado and extract the pit.'),
(937, 150, 7, 'Place the avocado flesh in a medium bowl and mash with a fork. Once youve broken it up a bit, add the garlic, lime juice, cilantro and salt. Mash the avocado until the seasoning is evenly distributed and you have a chunky paste. Set aside.'),
(938, 150, 8, 'Place each baked sweet potato in a shallow bowl.'),
(939, 150, 9, 'Cut along the top of the sweet potato and pull back the skin. Spilt the sweet potatoes a little bit to make room for the fillings.'),
(940, 150, 10, 'Divide the rice and bean mixture among the sweet potatoes (spillover is fine!). Top each bowl with th of the rustic salsa. Finish each plate with a dollop of the guacamole and some shredded cabbage on top.'),
(941, 150, 11, 'Serve with hot sauce on the side if you wish.'),
(944, 158, 1, 'In a heavy saucepan, heat chocolate chips, milk and marshmallow creme just until melted; stir until smooth (mixture will be thick).'),
(946, 158, 2, 'With tongs, immediately dip marshmallows, one at a time, in chocolate mixture; allow excess to drip off. Quickly roll in pecans.'),
(948, 158, 3, 'Place on waxed paper-lined baking sheets (Reheat chocolate mixture if necessary for easier coating.)'),
(949, 158, 4, 'Refrigerate until firm. Store in the refrigerator in an airtight container.'),
(950, 160, 1, 'On an unfloured surface, roll each breadstick into a 20-in. rope; twist into a pretzel shape.'),
(951, 160, 2, 'Place 2 in. apart on ungreased baking sheets.'),
(952, 160, 3, 'Brush with egg white and sprinkle with salt.'),
(953, 155, 1, 'In a small bowl, combine the first nine ingredients.'),
(954, 159, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.'),
(955, 155, 2, 'Pour 3/4 cup into a large resealable plastic bag; add salmon. Seal bag and turn to coat; refrigerate for 1 hour, turning occasionally. Set aside remaining marinade for basting.'),
(956, 159, 2, 'Whisk together the flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.In the bowl a stand mixer with the paddle attachment, cream the butter, white sugar and brown sugar together until light and fluffy.'),
(957, 162, 1, 'Boil potatoes in salted water until tender.'),
(958, 155, 3, 'Drain and discard marinade. Using long-handled tongs, moisten a paper towel with cooking oil and lightly coat the grill rack.'),
(959, 160, 4, 'Bake at 375° for 10-13 minutes or until lightly browned.'),
(960, 155, 4, 'Place salmon skin side down on rack. Grill, covered, over medium heat or broil over medium heat for 5 minutes.'),
(961, 159, 3, 'Add the eggs one at a time and scrape down the side of the bowl.'),
(962, 162, 2, 'Let cool.In large mixing bowl, add diced eggs, pickles, and celery.'),
(963, 160, 5, 'Remove to a wire rack. For mustard dip, combine the remaining ingredients in a small bowl.'),
