(965, 155, 5, 'Brush with reserved marinade. Grill or broil 15-20 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
(966, 159, 4, 'Add the vanilla.Alternate between the flour mixture and eggnog, adding until all of the ingredients are incorporated.'),
(967, 162, 3, 'Mix gently'),
(968, 160, 6, 'Serve with pretzels.'),
(969, 162, 4, 'Add cooled potatoes to egg mixture.When thoroughly combined, add mayonnaise and mustard. Gently mix.Salt and pepper to taste.Keep refrigerated until served'),
(970, 159, 5, 'Add the chocolate chips.Scoop the cookie dough onto the prepared baking sheets. I used a 2 tablespoons scoop.'),
(971, 161, 1, 'To your slow cooker, add the corn, jalapeo, red bell pepper, garlic, monterey jack cheese, sour cream, pale ale beer, cumin, chili powder, onion powder, and salt and pepper to taste. Stir to combine.Break the cream cheese into pieces and place on top of the corn mixture. Cover the slow cooker and cook for 4 hours on high or 6-8 hours on low. When you are ready to serve. Give the corn mixture a stir to incorporate the cream cheese.'),
(972, 156, 2, 'Score around themiddle of the potatoes, then bake themin their skins for about 1 hr or until soft.Halfway through, rub the whole garlicwith a little oil, then roast with thepotatoes for 25-30 mins until soft.'),
(973, 159, 6, 'Bake the cookies for 15 minutes, or until the edges are just starting to brown.'),
(974, 161, 2, 'Serve immediately, topped with bacon and green onions, with tortilla chips.Enjoy!'),
(975, 156, 3, 'Let the potatoes and garlic cool slightly.Halve and scoop out the flesh from thepotatoes (you need 300g). Push througha ricer, or mash well. Peel the garlic, pushthe flesh through a fine sieve, then gentlyfold into potatoes with the Parmesanand egg yolk, but don’t overwork themixture. Carefully fold in the flour, 2 tspoil, the capers, parsley and some seasoning,then gently work the dough into a ball.Bring a large pan of water to the boil.'),
(976, 159, 7, 'Whisk together the glaze ingredients and set aside.'),
(977, 156, 4, 'Place the dough on a work surface. Divideinto 28 pieces, then shape into small balls(about half the size of a golf ball). Blanch(in batches) in the boiling water for about2 mins or until the dumplings rise to thesurface.'),
(978, 156, 5, 'Remove with a slotted spoonand leave to dry on a clean tea towel.(To prepare 1-2 hrs ahead before frying,remove the dumplings from the boilingwater, then place them in a bowl oficed water. When cold, transfer to a teatowel to dry. Coat in a little of the extraoil in a large shallow dish to preventthem sticking together.)For the sauce, whisk the egg yolk,lemon zest and 1 tbsp juice in a smallbowl. Slowly pour in the oil in a thin,steady stream, whisking continuously,until you have a thick-ish mayonnaise.'),
(979, 159, 8, 'Transfer the cookies to a cooling rack. Once the cookies have cooled down, brush with glaze.'),
(980, 156, 6, 'Whisk in the cream, then pour in enoughof the fish stock to give a consistency thatwill coat the back of a spoon. Taste andseason with salt, pepper and more lemonjuice if needed. Chill until ready to serve.Will keep in the fridge for up to 2 days.When ready to serve, heat the grill tohigh. Lay the fish on 2 well-oiled bakingtrays and score the skin a few times.'),
(981, 156, 7, 'Brush a little oil over each fish andseason. Grill for about 10 mins, withoutturning, until the flesh comes easilyaway from the bone.While the fish cooks, fry the dumplings.'),
(982, 159, 9, 'Garnish with cinnamon sugar.'),
(983, 156, 8, 'Heat 1-2 tbsp olive oil in a non-stick fryingpan. Fry the dumplings, turning often,until golden brown.'),
(984, 156, 9, 'Remove with aslotted spoon and drain on kitchen paper.Keep warm. Bring a pan of water to theboil, cook the samphire for 2 mins, thendrain. Gently warm the lemon sauce in apan, then add the spinach and parsleyand allow to wilt.'),
(985, 156, 10, 'Place some samphireon each plate, lay the fish on top andseason with sea salt flakes. Arrangethe dumplings in a small pile and poura little sauce around the fish.'),
(986, 156, 11, 'Serve theremaining sauce separately.'),
(987, 164, 1, 'Lightly grease 6 holes of a muffin tin and preheat the oven to 350F/175C.'),
(988, 164, 2, 'Cut the fat off the bacon and slice the remaining meat up into small pieces.'),
(989, 164, 3, 'Place in a microwave-safe dish and cook in the microwave for around 2 minutes or until piping hot. Set to one side.In a separate microwave-safe dish, cook the frozen spinach in the microwave for around 5 minutes, or until fully defrosted. Squeeze out the excess water.'),
(990, 164, 4, 'Mix together the bacon pieces, spinach, eggs, milk, salt and pepper until fully combined.'),
(991, 164, 5, 'Pour the mixture into the prepared muffin tin and bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes or until golden and puffy. Eat straight away while hot.'),
(992, 163, 1, 'In a stand mixer, mix all the brioche dough ingredients. At first it will be a sticky mess, but have faith. After 20 minutes of kneading, you will have a gorgeous, shiny, buttery dough.Shape the dough into a ball and place it in a greased covered bowl to rise for an hour.Once the dough has risen, put it in the fridge for at least an hour to make it easier to shape, or overnight if you lack time.Peel the apples and remove the core.'),
(993, 163, 2, 'Cut into chunks roughly 1 inch square.Melt the butter in a medium saucepan.'),
(994, 169, 1, 'Position oven racks in the top and bottom thirds of the oven, and preheat to 375 degrees F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment.'),
(995, 163, 3, 'Add the brown sugar and stir to combine.'),
(996, 167, 1, 'You really are making hot chocolate at the start, so in a large mixing bowl, mix together the water, coconut milk, cocoa powder, vanilla, salt, sugar, and liquid stevia.'),
(997, 165, 1, 'Melt butter and semi-sweet chocolate together in the microwave. Cool slightly.'),
(998, 166, 1, '1'),
(999, 169, 2, 'Whisk together the flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl. Beat the butter and both sugars with an electric mixer on medium-high speed in a second large bowl until light and fluffy, about 4 minutes.'),
(1000, 163, 4, 'Add the apples and the vanilla. Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes, until apples are soft and caramel is bubbling.'),
(1001, 168, 1, 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees. On a large rimmed baking sheet, toss potatoes with 1 tablespoon oil; season with salt and pepper. Roast 10 minutes.'),
(1002, 167, 2, 'Mix well and pour into a greased 5-quart slow cooker.'),
(1003, 165, 2, 'Add chocolate mixture to a mixer bowl.'),
(1004, 166, 2, 'Set aside about 3 tablespoons coconut milk.'),
(1005, 169, 3, 'Add the eggs to the butter mixture, one at time, beating after each addition to incorporate; beat in the vanilla. Reduce the speed to medium, add the flour mixture, and beat until just incorporated. Stir in the chocolate chips.'),
(1006, 163, 5, 'Remove from heat and set aside. This will keep in the fridge overnight as well.When ready to bake, preheat your oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.'),
(1007, 167, 3, 'Pour in the steel-cut oats and give it a good whisk.Cook the oatmeal on LOW for 1-2 hours, then switch it over to KEEP WARM until you wake up in the morning and smell the coffee (or rather hot chocolate steel-cut oats). I\'ve cooked it as long as 12 hours and it was still great!'),
(1008, 165, 3, 'Add eggs and blend in.'),
(1009, 166, 3, 'Heat the rest in a medium saucepan or wok until small pools of oil appear on the surface.'),
(1010, 169, 4, 'Scoop 12 heaping tablespoons of dough onto each prepared baking sheet about 2 inches apart.'),
(1011, 163, 6, 'Remove the dough from the fridge and let it come to room temperature. Grease individual muffin tins. Fill each muffin hole with an inch and a half of dough. Press your fingers into the center of each brioche to push a well. Lay a heaping tablespoon of caramel apple mixture into each well.For each brioche, take another small ball of dough (about the size of a ping pong ball), flatten it in your palm, and stretch it out as thin as you can get it. Now lay it over the apple mixture and pinch the sides to cover completely. Repeat for each brioche. Finish by brushing the top of each brioche with an egg wash (1 egg yolk and 4 tablespoons of heavy cream).'),
(1012, 165, 4, 'Add sugar, vanilla and beat for 2 minutes.'),
(1013, 166, 4, 'Add the curry paste and stir well to incorporate. Cook until aromatic, 4-5 minutes.'),
(1014, 169, 5, 'Roll each into a ball with slightly wet hands.'),
(1015, 157, 1, 'Combine ingredients in a small bowl and let sit for several hours in the fridge, allowing the flavors to marry.To make the rice: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.'),
(1016, 157, 2, 'Add ginger, garlic, and cinnamon stick, and saut 1 minute, or until fragrant. Stir in rice, and saut 2 minutes, or until rice grains are opaque.'),
(1017, 169, 6, 'Bake until the cookies are golden but still soft in the center, 12 to 15 minutes, rotating the baking sheets halfway through.'),
(1018, 166, 5, '2'),
(1019, 165, 5, 'Add the flour and salt and beat until flour is incorporated.Spray 8 dishes (I used small canning jars) with cooking spray. Divide the brownie mixture up between the 8 containers, filling no more than 3/4 full.'),
(1020, 163, 7, 'Bake in the oven for 25-30 minutes, until golden brown.These are delicious warm or cold.'),
(1021, 165, 6, 'Add a peanut butter cup.'),
(1022, 166, 6, 'Add the beef and simmer until nearly cooked through, about 2 minutes.'),
(1023, 169, 7, 'Let the cookies cool for a few minutes on the baking sheets, then transfer them to a rack to cool completely.'),
(1024, 157, 3, 'Add coconut milk, water, sugar, salt, lime zest, and white pepper; bring to a simmer. Stir once, cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer 15 minutes (adjust cook time according to directions on rice packaging). Fluff rice with fork, cover, and let rest 5 minutes.To make the chili: Rub all but 2 tablespoons of jerk seasoning over surface of chicken on all sides.'),
(1025, 165, 7, 'Bake in a 350 degree oven for 20 - 25 minutes. Brownies will rise above the canning jars.'),
(1026, 166, 7, 'Add  bell pepper, fish sauce, and sugar.'),
(1027, 169, 8, 'When the baking sheets have cooled completely, scoop the remaining dough onto 1 sheet and bake. Store the cookies in a tightly sealed container at room temperature for up to 5 days.'),
(1028, 157, 4, 'Heat a large pot over medium heat and add 1 tablespoon oil. Once hot, add the chicken and cook 8-10 minutes or until cooked through.'),
(1029, 165, 8, 'Let cool before adding peanut butter filling.Whip the heavy cream, confectioner\'s sugar and peanut butter together. It will not get stiff and will set up in the refrigerator. Do this while the brownies are baking. Refrigerate until ready to use. There will be a slight depression in the brownies, add the peanut butter filling into the cavity after the brownies are cooled. Top with whipped cream and another peanut butter cup.'),
(1030, 166, 8, 'Let simmer for a few minutes, then taste, adding fish sauce or sugar as needed.'),
(1031, 157, 5, 'Remove to a cutting board and allow to cool to touch. Dice or shred using 2 forks and set aside.Meanwhile, heat remaining 2 tablespoons of oil in the same pot. Once hot, add onion and bell peppers. Cook until softened and beginning to brown, about 10 minutes.'),
(1032, 166, 9, 'Add kaffir lime (if using basil, do not add until step'),
(1033, 157, 6, 'Add ginger, garlic, scotch bonnet/habanero, all-spice, paprika, cumin, cinnamon, and chili powder; stir continuously for 30-60 seconds.'),
(1034, 166, 10, 'and simmer until aromatic, 1 to 2 minutes longer.'),
(1035, 157, 7, 'Add the molasses, liquid smoke, tomatoes, beans, and chicken broth. Bring to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes over low heat.'),
(1036, 166, 11, '3'),
(1037, 157, 8, 'Add diced/shredded chicken and cook for 15 minutes longer.To serve, place rice on bottom of bowl. Cover with chili and top with a dollop of mango salsa.'),
(1038, 166, 12, 'Remove from heat and top with peanuts, chile pepper, and fresh basil leaves if using.  Spoon the reserved coconut milk over top and serve with rice.'),
(1039, 171, 1, '1'),
(1040, 172, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees.'),
(1041, 178, 1, 'Place all ingredients in a blender and process until smooth.'),
(1042, 174, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone baking sheet.'),
(1043, 171, 2, 'In 2-quart saucepan, mix all ingredients.'),
(1044, 172, 2, 'Mix together the cake mix, pudding mix, soda, oil and eggs until smooth.For stability, place each ketchup cup in the well on a mini cupcake tin, otherwise use a cookie sheet.Fill each cup three-fourths full.'),
(1045, 177, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.In the bowl of a food processor, process ½ cup of the oats until they make a fine powder, about 1 to 2 minutes (you\'ll have made oat flour). Dump oat flour into a large bowl.'),
(1046, 172, 3, 'Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.'),
(1047, 174, 2, 'In a mixing bowl on medium speed, cream together the vegetable oil and sugar until light and fluffy.'),
(1048, 172, 4, 'Place on cooling rack to cool completely.Whip together the cream cheese pudding mix, cream cheese and butter until fluffy.'),
(1049, 174, 3, 'Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.'),
(1050, 170, 1, 'Grease a 9 inch springform pan. Securely wrap with a double layer of heavy duty aluminum foil completely covering the bottom and sides of pan and set aside.'),
(1051, 177, 2, 'Add remaining oats, ground flaxseed, salt, baking powder and cinnamon, if using. Stir to combine; set aside.In a smaller bowl, whisk together mashed banana, peanut butter, maple syrup, oil, vanilla extract and chocolate chips.'),
(1052, 171, 3, 'Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Simmer uncovered about 1 hour, stirring frequently, until thickened.'),
(1053, 174, 4, 'Add the anisette liquor and mix to combine. Reduce the speed to low and gradually add the flour mixture, mixing until just combined.'),
(1054, 172, 5, 'Add vanilla and combine.Gradually beat in sugar 1 cup at a time.'),
(1055, 170, 2, 'Mix together cookie crumbs, melted butter sugar and salt and press in the bottom and up the sides of springform. Chill.In a large mixing bowl beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.'),
(1056, 177, 3, 'Add wet ingredients to dry and mix with spatula to incorporate.Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto baking sheet and bake for 12-13 minutes.'),
(1057, 171, 4, '2'),
(1058, 176, 1, 'In a small saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour until smooth; gradually add milk. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.'),
(1059, 175, 1, '1'),
(1060, 174, 5, 'Add the pecans and mix briefly to combine.'),
(1061, 170, 3, 'Add eggs and beat just until yellow disappears. On low add flour and nutmeg and vanilla extract and blend just until combined.'),
(1062, 173, 1, 'In a bowl, crush together the garlic and salt. To prepare the dressing, mix in olive oil, lemon juice, vinegar, ginger, cumin, and cayenne pepper.'),
(1063, 177, 4, 'Let cool on pan for a few minutes, then transfer to a cooling rack.'),
(1064, 171, 5, 'Cool 1 hour, stirring occasionally.'),
(1065, 176, 2, 'Remove from the heat; cool for 15 minutes.'),
(1066, 175, 2, 'For the Crust: Using a food processor, pulse together flour, sugar, salt, rosewater, and lard until the dough pulls away from the sides of the mixer and easily forms a ball. Press the dough into pie plate.'),
(1067, 174, 6, 'Turn out the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead briefly to make sure the nuts are incorporated.'),
(1068, 170, 4, 'Pour half of batter into prepared crust.Leaving a half inch border along the sides, add cranberry sauce gently in a thin layer.Top with remaining batter.'),
(1069, 171, 6, 'Serve chutney at room temperature for best flavor. Cover and refrigerate up to 2 weeks.'),
(1070, 173, 2, 'In a separate bowl, stir together the garbanzo beans, yellow bell peppers, green onions, and cilantro.'),
(1071, 176, 3, 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the cottage cheese, baking powder, mustard and salt. In a large bowl, beat eggs. Slowly beat in the cream cheese, cottage cheese mixture and white sauce until smooth. Fold in the Jarlsberg and Parmesan cheeses.'),
(1072, 175, 3, '2'),
(1073, 174, 7, 'Divide the dough into two pieces and form each into a log approximately 12 inches by 3 inches.'),
(1074, 170, 5, 'Place foil wrapped springform in a large baking dish with tall sides.'),
(1075, 173, 3, 'Mix in the dressing. Cover, and chill in the refrigerator 8 hours, or overnight.'),
(1076, 176, 4, 'Pour into a greased 9-in. pie plate.'),
(1077, 175, 4, 'Adjust oven rack to center position and preheat oven to 375°F. Par-bake empty crust until golden brown, about 7 minutes.'),
(1078, 174, 8, 'Place both on the baking sheet and bake for about 25 minutes, or until lightly browned on top.'),
(1079, 170, 6, 'Pour very hot water as far as possible in the baking dish.'),
(1080, 176, 5, 'Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.'),
(1081, 175, 5, '3'),
(1082, 174, 9, 'Remove from the oven and let rest for about 20 minutes. Reduce the oven temperature to 300 degrees F. Slice the logs on the diagonal, about ½ to ¾-inch in width.'),
(1083, 170, 7, 'Bake at 350F for approximately 1 hour or until set.Allow to cool slightly (if serving warm) and top with sugared cranberries prior to serving. If serving cold, refrigerate until ready to serve.Bring water and 2 cups sugar to a low simmer and stir occasionally until sugar is completely dissolved.Turn off heat and add cranberries, being careful not to get liquid too hot as the cranberries will begin to pop.'),
(1084, 176, 6, 'Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.'),
(1085, 175, 6, 'For the Filling: Using an electric hand mixer or stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, beat together together butter and sugar until fluffy, about 3 minutes.'),
(1086, 174, 10, 'Place the biscotti back on the baking sheet and bake for an additional 20 minutes, turned them once halfway through baking.'),
(1087, 170, 8, 'Transfer to a medium mixing bowl and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.'),
(1088, 176, 7, 'Serve warm. Refrigerate leftovers.'),
(1089, 175, 7, 'Add cream and eggs, beating until smooth, then stir in flour and vanilla with a large spatula.'),
(1090, 174, 11, 'Remove from the oven and let cool to room temperature before storing.'),
(1091, 170, 9, 'Drain liquid reserving for another use.'),
(1092, 175, 8, 'Pour filling into crust.'),
(1093, 170, 10, 'Place cranberries on a shallow baking dish and gently toss with super fine sugar to coat completely.'),
(1094, 175, 9, 'Bake until a golden brown crust forms on top, about 40 minutes.'),
(1095, 170, 11, 'Spread out in a single layer and allow to cool about an hour.In medium sauce pot bring water, sugar and cranberries to a low boil stirring occasionally. Cook until they begin to pop and congeal, about 10 minutes. Allow to cool.'),
(1096, 175, 10, '4'),
(1097, 175, 11, 'For the Glaze: While pie bakes, bring water and sugar to a boil in a small saucepan, stirring constantly for until the mixture coats the back of a spoon, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
(1098, 175, 12, 'Remove the syrup from the heat, stir in lime juice and rose water.'),
(1099, 175, 13, 'Drizzle over pie while still warm.'),
(1100, 180, 1, 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.'),
(1101, 180, 2, 'Cut the French bread.  It can be cut in half lengthwise, cut into quarters, or cut into thick slices; however you prefer.  Soften the butter by letting it sit out before using it or by putting it in the microwave for just a few seconds.'),
(1102, 180, 3, 'Spread the butter over the bread with a spatula.  Then sprinkle the garlic powder over the butter.  Using the spatula, spread the garlic powder evenly over the bread.  Next, sprinkle the paprika over the butter and garlic and spread it evenly over the bread.'),
(1103, 180, 4, 'Add the parsley flakes and spread evenly over the top of the bread.  Top with the grated parmesan cheese and lightly spread it over the top of the bread.  Wrap the garlic bread in foil and set on a cookie sheet.'),
(1104, 188, 1, 'Quarter the biscuits; place in a greased 13-in. x 9-in. baking dish. Top with picante sauce, green pepper, onion and olives.'),
(1105, 180, 5, 'Bake in the oven for about 10 minutes then open the foil up so garlic bread will toast.  Continue baking in the oven for another 5 to 8 minutes until the bread is hot all the way through and the top is slightly toasted.'),
(1106, 185, 1, 'Preheat oven to 400F.'),
(1107, 181, 1, 'Combine all the ingredients in a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment and blend until evenly mixed.'),
(1108, 188, 2, 'Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.'),
(1109, 180, 6, 'Serve hot right out of the oven.'),
(1110, 185, 2, 'Cut two pieces of parchment paper the size of a baking sheet. Arrange half of the asparagus spears on the center of one piece of parchment paper and situate one salmon filet on top of the asparagus.'),
(1111, 181, 2, 'Pour cheese ball onto a sheet of plastic wrap and place another sheet of plastic wrap on top. Form the cheese into a ball (or whatever shape you want), and then chill for 20 to 30 minutes.'),
(1112, 188, 3, 'Bake 10 minutes longer or until the cheese is melted.'),
(1113, 185, 3, 'Drizzle the salmon with one tablespoon of the olive oil and sprinkle with  teaspoon of the Stone House Seasoning. Arrange 3 slices of lemon on top of the salmon.Fold the sides of the parchment paper toward the salmon. Gather the ends of the parchment paper and pull toward the center of the salmon. Fold down one time and then wrap the parchment paper underneath the salmon to secure.Repeat with the second filet.'),
(1114, 181, 3, 'Serve with butter crackers and fresh cut veggies!'),
(1115, 187, 1, 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees.'),
(1116, 185, 4, 'Bake in the oven for 15 minutes.'),
(1117, 182, 1, '1 In a 3 or 4 quart saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon butter on medium heat.'),
(1118, 182, 2, 'Add the shallots and cook for a minute or two, until translucent.'),
(1119, 187, 2, 'Place sweet potatoes on a baking sheet and bake in oven for about an hour, until tender. Allow to cool slightly.'),
(1120, 184, 1, 'Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).'),
(1121, 185, 5, 'Remove from the oven. The salmon is done when it flakes easily with a fork.'),
(1122, 182, 3, 'Add the rice and cook for 2 minutes more, stirring until nicely coated.2 While the shallots are cooking, bring the stock to a simmer in a saucepan.3'),
(1123, 187, 3, 'Remove skin from potatoes. Mash in a large bowl with a potato masher or ricer. Stir in vanilla milk, brown sugar and spices.'),
(1124, 184, 2, 'Place a small pan containing about 2-3 cups of hot water onto the bottom of your oven ( directly onto the bottom of the oven) to generate steam. Lightly grease a large baking sheet with shortening and then dust lightly with flour. Use a 10 inch pan as a template and draw a 10 inch circle onto the flour dusted sheet using a toothpick. Set aside.'),
(1125, 183, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 350F. Line a loaf pan with parchment paper and set aside.'),
(1126, 182, 4, 'Add the wine.  Slowly stir, allowing the rice to absorb the wine.  Once the wine is almost completely absorbed, add 1/2 cup of hot stock to the rice.  Continue to stir until the liquid is almost completely absorbed, adding more stock in 1/2 cup increments.  Stir often to prevent the rice from sticking to the bottom of the pan. Continue cooking and stirring rice, adding a little bit of broth at a time, cooking and stirring until it is absorbed, until the rice is tender, but still firm to the bite, about 20-25 minutes.  With the last ladle of stock, add the asparagus. Turn off the heat.Note the stock amount given is approximate.  You may need a little more or less.  If you end up needing more stock and you find yourself without, just use water.4 Gently stir in the Parmesan cheese and the remaining 1 tablespoon butter.'),
(1127, 189, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F. For easy cleanup line a large roasting pan (large enough to comfortably fit all the ingredients in a single layer) with aluminum foil. (I like to use a half sheet pan.)'),
(1128, 184, 3, 'Place the 4 eggs into a small measuring cup and mix with a fork to combine, set aside.'),
(1129, 183, 2, 'Add the dry ingredients to the bowl of a food processor and pulse to combine.'),
(1130, 182, 5, 'Add salt and pepper to taste.'),
(1131, 189, 2, 'Place the sausage, potatoes, peppers, onions and garlic (if using) in the pan.'),
(1132, 186, 1, 'In a deep bowl, beat the eggs and oil for 1 minute and they should get bubbly.'),
(1133, 184, 4, 'Combine the milk, water, salt and butter in a saucepan over medium heat. When it comes to a full boil, add the flour all at once and stir to make a paste. Continue to stir over the heat for about 40 seconds until the paste dries a little.'),
(1134, 182, 6, 'Serve immediately.'),
(1135, 183, 3, 'Add eggs, oil, syrup and vinegar and process until smooth.'),
(1136, 189, 3, 'Drizzle the olive oil over the ingredients. Season with the oregano, salt and pepper. Toss to coat everything with the oil and seasonings. Roast in the oven until the potatoes are tender and the sausage is browned, 45 to 60 minutes, stirring the mixture every 20 minutes or so.'),
(1137, 186, 2, 'Add cake mix powder, vanilla pudding and orange juice.'),
(1138, 184, 5, 'Remove from heat and place paste into a mixing bowl.'),
(1139, 183, 4, 'Transfer batter to prepared loaf tin and bake on the center rack for 25 - 35 minutes (mine took 3'),
(1140, 186, 3, 'Mix until everything is combined.'),
(1141, 184, 6, 'Let cool about 4 minutes.With a mixer on low, mix the paste and slowly add the beaten eggs.'),
(1142, 183, 5, 'until the top has turned golden brown and a cake tester inserted into the center comes out clean.Cool in the pan for 1 hour then transfer to a wire rack and cool completely before slicing.'),
(1143, 186, 4, 'Add vanilla extract, orange extract and orange zest and mix again until everything is blended properly. You can add chocolate chips or cashews or coconut or cranberries at the point.'),
(1144, 184, 7, 'Mix slowly but thoroughly until all of the eggs have been added.'),
(1145, 186, 5, 'Pour this batter into an 8×3 round cake pan.'),
(1146, 184, 8, 'Place the paste into a pastry bag fitted with a 1/2 inch round decorating tip. Pipe the paste out onto the sheet pan following the 10 inch ring you outlined. Pipe a second ring around the inside next to this ring. Finally, pipe another ring on top of these two rings. Lightly paint the set of rings with the remaining 1 beaten egg and press the sliced almonds into the paste.'),
(1147, 186, 6, 'Bake at 350 degrees for 45- 50 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.'),
(1148, 184, 9, 'Place in the oven on the lowest shelf and bake at 425 degrees F (220 degrees C) for 20 minutes. Reduce the temperature to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) and bake about 12 minutes more or until brown.'),
(1149, 186, 7, 'Add butter and cream cheese in a deep bowl and mix until it’s properly combined and there are no lumps.'),
(1150, 184, 10, 'Remove form the oven and using a long serrated knife slice off the top half of the puffed ring.'),
(1151, 186, 8, 'Add orange zest, orange extract and orange jam.'),
(1152, 184, 11, 'Remove any bits of raw dough on the inside of the ring. Replace the top and place back in the oven to crisp the dough, about 5 more minutes. Cool on a rack.To Make The Filling: Whip the pastry cream until smooth.'),
(1153, 186, 9, 'Mix for a few seconds again. Keep in mind over-mixing can cause your frosting to break down.'),
(1154, 184, 12, 'Place the heavy cream into a bowl along with the vanilla and beat on high until soft peaks are formed.'),
(1155, 186, 10, 'Add powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time and keep mixing until your frosting is smooth and creamy.'),
(1156, 186, 11, 'Spread on your cake immediately or keep it in the refrigerator until needed.'),
(1157, 186, 12, 'Cut out thin round orange slices.'),
(1158, 186, 13, 'Place them on a tray lined with some tissue paper so the juices get absorbed and don’t leak all over your cake.Once your cake has cooled , cut it in half.Fill it with frosting.Gently place the top half of the cake on top of this frosting.'),
(1159, 186, 14, 'Spread some more frosting on top of the cake.Arrange your orange slices in a circular pattern on top of the cake. Sprinkle some orange zest all over the top and add a few leaves wherever you like.'),
(1160, 194, 1, 'Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.'),
(1161, 194, 2, 'Place Oreo cookies into a plastic zip top bag and crush using the back of a wooden spoon or a rolling pin until the Oreos are fine crumbs.'),
(1162, 194, 3, 'Pour all but  cup of the crumbs into a medium bowl.'),
(1163, 194, 4, 'Add the cream cheese and mix until well blended. Scoop mixture by the tablespoon and roll in between your palms to form into balls.'),
(1164, 191, 1, 'Place ham on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Cover and bake at 325° for 1-3/4 hours.'),
(1165, 195, 1, 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.Blend together cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy.'),
(1166, 194, 5, 'Place the chocolate chip and coconut oil in a microwave safe bowl and microwave in 10 second increments until fully melted and smooth when stirred. Alternately, you can also melt together in a small saucepan over medium-low heat.Dip the balls in chocolate and place onto the parchment paper lined baking sheet. Sprinkle with reserved  cup cookie crumbs.Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour. Store leftover truffles, covered, in refrigerator or place in an airtight container and freeze for up 3 months. To serve, allow to thaw in the refrigerator.'),
(1167, 191, 2, 'In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients until blended.'),
(1168, 195, 2, 'Add in cheddar and Mexican cheese blend cheeses, jalapenos, and bacon crumbles.'),
(1169, 191, 3, 'Pour over the ham.'),
(1170, 195, 3, 'Combine well.'),
(1171, 191, 4, 'Bake, uncovered, 30-45 minutes longer or until a meat thermometer reads 140°.'),
(1172, 195, 4, 'Pour into a casserole dish and bake 15 minutes.'),
(1173, 195, 5, 'Add remaining cup of Mexican cheese on top of dip and return to oven for 10 minutes to melt cheese.'),
(1174, 195, 6, 'Serve with corn chips, tortilla chips or a spoon!'),
(1175, 192, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350F. Toss bread with oil and spread on a baking sheet.'),
(1176, 190, 1, 'Rinse the rice under running water.'),
(1177, 192, 2, 'Bake, turning once, until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
(1178, 190, 2, 'Place the uncooked rice, chicken breasts, onions, celery, carrots, garlic, bay leaves, chicken broth, 21 Seasoning Salute, salt, and pepper in a slow cooker. Cover and cook on the high for 3-4 hours or on the low for 7-8 hours.With  hour of slow cooking remaining, remove the chicken from the slow cooker. Allow to cool slightly before shredding using two forks; set aside.'),
(1179, 197, 1, '1'),
(1180, 192, 3, 'Cut 1 tomato in half. Working over a large bowl, shred both halves using the large holes on a box grater. Discard the skin.'),
(1181, 190, 3, 'Heat the butter and oil in a saucepan. Once the butter is melted, add the flour and let the mixture cook for 1 minute.'),
(1182, 197, 2, 'Toast bread to desired level of doneness. Top with refried beans and avocado (mash with a fork if desired).'),
(1183, 192, 4, 'Add mayonnaise, chives (or scallion greens), vinegar, garlic powder and pepper; whisk to combine.Chop the remaining 3 tomatoes.'),
(1184, 190, 4, 'Whisk the mixture slowly while adding in the milk. Continue to whisk until all lumps have dissolved. Cook mixture 5-6 minutes or until thick and creamy.'),
(1185, 197, 3, 'Add slivered onions, sprinkle with salt, and serve.'),
(1186, 192, 5, 'Add the tomatoes, romaine and croutons to the bowl with the dressing; toss to coat. Sprinkle with bacon.'),
(1187, 190, 5, 'Add this creamy mixture to the slow cooker; stir. Return shredded chicken to the crock pot, cover, and cook an additional 5-10 minutes.'),
(1188, 193, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350F. Line a muffin tin with paper liners. Set aside.'),
(1189, 190, 6, 'Serve hot.'),
(1190, 193, 2, 'Place the stout and butter in a large, heavy saucepan, and heat until the butter melts.'),
(1191, 193, 3, 'Remove the pan from the heat, and add the cocoa powder.'),
(1192, 196, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350°F.'),
(1193, 193, 4, 'Whisk until the mixture is smooth. Set aside to cool to room temperature.In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a large bowl; set aside.In another large mixing bowl, beat together the eggs and sour cream.'),
(1194, 196, 2, 'Grease an 8-inch square baking pan with non-stick spray or softened butter. Line the pan with parchment paper; grease parchment paper (this ensures easy removal of brownies).'),
(1195, 193, 5, 'Add the cooled stout-cocoa mixture, mixing to combine.'),
(1196, 196, 3, 'Place butter, chocolate, cocoa powder and 3 tablespoons of crushed candy canes (reserve the rest for the layering steps) in a heatproof medium bowl set over a pan of simmering water. Stir until butter and chocolate are melted. The candy canes will not completely melt, so small specks will remain in chocolate mixture.'),
(1197, 193, 6, 'Add the flour mixture and mix together at slow speed. Scrape the sides and bottom of the bowl, and mix again for 1 minute.Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.'),
(1198, 196, 4, 'Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.'),
(1199, 193, 7, 'Bake for 20 - 22 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Repeat with remaining batter.Cool completely on a wire rack before frosting.Beat butter until light and fluffy. Slowly add cocoa powder, powdered sugar, milk, and vanilla sugar. Beat until everything is incorporated.'),
(1200, 196, 5, 'In a separate bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside.'),
(1201, 193, 8, 'Add more powdered sugar or milk if you want a different consistency. Frost cupcakes once cooled.'),
(1202, 196, 6, 'Place both kinds of sugar, eggs, and vanilla in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the whisk attachment, and beat on medium speed until pale and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Carefully add the chocolate mixture and beat until combined.'),
(1203, 196, 7, 'Add flour mixture and beat, stopping to scrape down the sides of the bowls as needed, until ingredients are combined.'),
(1204, 196, 8, 'Pour half of the batter into prepared baking pan. Break the chocolate bars into squares and place them, evenly spaced, around the top of the brownie batter. Sprinkle with half of the reserved candy cane pieces. Top with the remaining batter and sprinkle the remaining candy cane pieces on top.'),
(1205, 196, 9, 'Bake for about 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the brownies comes out with a few crumbs but is not wet. Allow the brownies to cool in the pan for 5 minutes. Lift the brownies out using the parchment paper and allow to completely cool on wire rack.'),
(1206, 196, 10, 'Cut into 16 brownies. Eat and repeat.'),
(1207, 199, 1, 'Remove lamb from the refrigerator 1 hour before starting to bring it to room temperature.'),
(1208, 198, 1, 'Finely chop the stems of the mushrooms. Set the caps aside. In a large saucepan, melt 5 tablespoons of the butter, and sauté the onions and garlic over medium heat until translucent, about 2 minutes.'),
(1209, 206, 1, 'Heat the grill to high. Arrange the baconon a baking tray lined with foil. Cook for5-7 mins until crisp, then turn off the grillbut leave the tray inside to keep warm.In a bowl, mix the flour, baking powderand sugar with a pinch of salt. Make awell in the centre and add the mashedbanana, eggs, butter and milk.'),
(1210, 199, 2, 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.'),
(1211, 198, 2, 'Add the chopped mushroom stems, and sauté a minute longer. Season with salt.'),
(1212, 206, 2, 'Whisk toa smooth batter without any flour lumps.'),
(1213, 202, 1, 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees and lightly spray a sheet pan with olive oil. Set aside.'),
(1214, 199, 3, 'Put the salt, black peppercorns, fennel seeds and cumin seeds in a spice grinder (or use a mortar and pestle) to roughly grind.'),
(1215, 206, 3, 'Heat a little butter in a large frying pan.Once sizzling, ladle in small dollops ofthe pancake batter, leaving a little spacebetween each, as they will spread out.Put 2 or 3 slices of banana onto the surfaceof each pancake and cook for 2 mins overa medium heat. When you see bubblesappear between the banana slices, flip thepancakes over and cook for 1 min more, until puffed up and golden.'),
(1216, 198, 3, 'Add the rice. Stir well to coat, then add 1 cup of stock and stir until the liquid is mostly absorbed.'),
(1217, 202, 2, 'Cut sweet potato and carrot into 3 or 4 large chunks.'),
(1218, 199, 4, 'Rub the outside of the lamb with the garlic. Sprinkle half of the rub over one side of the lamb in a thick layer.'),
(1219, 206, 4, 'Transfer toa plate and keep warm with the baconwhile you cook the rest.'),
(1220, 198, 4, 'Add another cup of stock, stirring constantly, and allow the rice to absorb it.Continue adding stock cup by cup, until all liquid is used and rice is tender, but still a little firm to the bite in the middle (about 25 minutes).Stir in remaining 1 tablespoon butter and the cheese, and season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Set aside.Slice the portobello caps paper-thin. Divide risotto into 4 bowls, immediately sprinkle with the shaved portobellos, and garnish with scallions and a drizzle (about 2 teaspoons) of truffle oil (or other flavored oil).'),
(1221, 202, 3, 'Place them in a food processor fitted with a metal blade and process until finely chopped into rice-size pieces.'),
(1222, 199, 5, 'Heat a cast iron skillet over medium heat until very hot.'),
(1223, 206, 5, 'Serve thepancakes with the crispy bacon anda drizzle of maple syrup.'),
(1224, 202, 4, 'Heat a large skillet over medium heat, spray the pan with oil and add the chopped vegetables. Cook, stirring for 5 minutes, until softened.'),
(1225, 199, 6, 'Add a splash of olive oil and place the lamb in the pan, seasoned side down. Sprinkle the remaining rub on the other side of the lamb.'),
(1226, 202, 5, 'Transfer to a large bowl with the egg, panko, mozzarella, onion powder, garlic powder, smoked paprika, salt and pepper and stir with a spatula to ensure it is evenly combined.With your hands, gently form sweet potato-carrot mixture into small rectangular pieces, pressing and rolling them firmly together about 1 tablespoon each. Evenly space them on prepared sheet pan, spray with olive oil and bake for 10 minutes.'),
(1227, 199, 7, 'Saute until brown and seared, 5 to 6 minutes, then flip and repeat on the other side.'),
(1228, 202, 6, 'Remove from oven, using your hands or small spatula, flip each over, put them back in the oven and bake for 10-12 more minutes, or until brown and crisp. Makes 30 tots.'),
(1229, 199, 8, 'Put the pan in the oven and roast until desired doneness (135 degrees F for medium).'),
(1230, 199, 9, 'Remove the pan from the oven and let sit for 15 minutes (it should come up to 145 degrees F for medium while it rests).'),
(1231, 199, 10, 'Slice the lamb and serve with mint jelly.'),
(1232, 200, 1, 'Prepare pie crust recipe (see notes). Divide dough in half, shape into 2 discs about 5-inches in diameter and 3/4-inch thick. Wrap in plastic. Refrigerate at least 1 hour (or up to 2 days), or freeze up to 1 month.On a lightly floured surface use a lightly floured rolling pin to roll out one disc of chilled dough to a 12-inch round, a generous 1/8-inch thick. Carefully fold dough in half, and slide it onto the rolling pin.'),
(1233, 200, 2, 'Transfer to a 9-inch pie pan. Unfold the dough, easing it gently into the pie pan; do not stretch the dough.Fold the overhan inder creating a double thick rim. Crimp the edge decoratively with your fingers and use a fork to prick the bottom of the dough in several spots. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Save second disc of dough for another purpose.'),
(1234, 205, 1, 'Heat a large skillet to medium high heat and add 2 teaspoons olive oil.'),
(1235, 207, 1, 'Rinse and sort through the beans, discarding any rocks or debris. Set aside. Reserve seasoning packet for later.'),
(1236, 200, 3, 'Place oven rack in middle and bottom positions. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.Cover prepared pie shell with parchment, leaving a bit of overhang, and add enough pie weights or dried beans to cover bottom.'),
(1237, 205, 2, 'Add vegetables and saut for 6-7 minutes or until tender. Using kitchen shears cut in a few places to avoid super long zucchini pieces. After veggies become tender and start to release water, take the pan to the sink and using a lid drain of excess water. Return to burner, turn off heat and stir in garlic powder, dried rosemary, salt and pepper.While veggies cook, use a smaller skillet and cook eggs to your desired preference, sunny side up, over easy or over hard.Divide vegetable mixture among plates, top with one or two eggs.'),
(1238, 207, 2, 'Dice the onion and celery. Peel and shred or finely dice the carrots. Mince the garlic.'),
(1239, 200, 4, 'Bake on center rack for 15 minutes.'),
(1240, 204, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Toss the pumpkin with a drizzle of olive oil and a generous amount of salt on several rimmed cookie sheets. Roast in the oven for 40-45 minutes, redistributing occasionally, until tender and beginning to brown.'),
(1241, 207, 3, 'Add the oil to a large stock pot over medium heat. When hot, stir in the onion, celery, and carrot.'),
(1242, 200, 5, 'Remove parchment and weights, and bake and center rack until barely golden, about 5 more minutes.'),
(1243, 211, 1, 'Preheat your grill on high.Using ¼ cup of basil pesto, brush chicken breasts with pesto.Grill the chicken breasts until cooked through (the insides reaching 160 degrees Fahrenheit). Before you bring the chicken inside, place 2 slices of cheese on each chicken breast and close the lid of the grill to let it melt.To assemble the sandwich: place one chicken breast on one slice of bread, top with bit of the remaining basil pesto then top with 1 tablespoon of sundried tomatoes.'),
(1244, 204, 2, 'Remove and set aside in a mixing bowl.In a large Dutch oven or casserole, melt the butter over medium heat.'),
(1245, 211, 2, 'Place the other slice of bread on top. Repeat with the other sandwich.'),
(1246, 207, 4, 'Cook vegetables until softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the garlic and cook 30 more seconds.'),
(1247, 200, 6, 'Transfer to a wire rack to cool.Reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees F. In a small bowl, combine pecans with 1 tablespoon butter and salt.'),
(1248, 204, 3, 'Add the leeks and sauté for 5-10 minutes until the butter is incorporated and they begin to wilt.'),
(1249, 207, 5, 'Add the chicken broth to the pot along with the dried beans.'),
(1250, 200, 7, 'Spread on a baking pan and toast until fragrant, 8 to 10 minutes. Set aside to cool.Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine sugar, corn syrup, rum, vanilla, and remaining butter. Stir in eggs.'),
(1251, 203, 1, '1'),
(1252, 204, 4, 'Add 1/2 cup  stock, turn the flame to low, cover and cook for 20-25 minutes stirring occasionally. Cook slowly until the leeks are completely soft and beginning to turn to mush. Take the lid off and cook uncovered until most of the liquid has evaporated. Season with salt and add to the pumpkin mixture.In the same pot or pan, add a little olive oil, turn the heat to medium- high, and add the onion, fennel, and thyme to the pot and sauté for 10 minutes. When tender, but not caramelized, add the white wine and season with salt and pepper. Continue to sauté for another 5 minutes or so until the vegetables are very tender and the alcohol in the wine has burned off.'),
(1253, 207, 6, 'Bring to a boil over medium heat, reduce to a simmer, and cover with a lid. Cook for 2 hours or until beans are mostly tender.'),
(1254, 200, 8, 'Add toasted pecans.'),
(1255, 203, 2, 'Dry the tofu slices with paper towels, and then cut into 1/2-inch thick rectangular slabs.'),
(1256, 204, 5, 'Add to the pumpkin-leek mixture.NOTE: everything up to this point can be done 1-2 days before.The day of, combine the garlic with 1/4 cup of olive oil.'),
(1257, 207, 7, 'Add the ham, salt, pepper, and reserved seasoning packet to the soup. Continue simmering for 30 minutes to an hour more, or until beans are tender.'),
(1258, 200, 9, 'Pour filling into cooled crust. Cover lightly with foil.'),
(1259, 203, 3, 'Heat = oil in a large wok over high heat until just starting to smoke.'),
(1260, 204, 6, 'Heat in the microwave until the oil is fragrant and infused, about 1-2 minutes. Toss the cubed ciabatta with the oil and a generous amount of salt and turn out onto several rimmed cookie sheets. Toast in a 350 degree oven for 5 minutes—until the bread is crisp, but not completely browned.Toss the bread together with the vegetable mixture, the eggs, stock, and parsley. Make sure it is well combined, and add any stock as necessary to make sure the bread is moist.'),
(1261, 207, 8, 'Add additional broth as desired.'),
(1262, 200, 10, 'Bake on the bottom rack for 20 minutes.'),
(1263, 208, 1, 'Preheat your oven to 350F (176C), and lightly grease a 9 x 5 (23cm x 13cm) bread pan.In a large mixing bowl, lightly beat the eggs until the yolks break apart.'),
(1264, 203, 4, 'Add the tofu slices tongs. Cook until golden, flipping occasionally, about 3 minutes.'),
(1265, 204, 7, 'Let stand for at least an hour so the flavors absorb. Then return to the oven and cook, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover, and cook for another 20-30 minutes until the top is crusty and brown.'),
(1266, 200, 11, 'Remove foil then continue to bake until the center of the pie feels gelatin-like when pressed with the back of a spoon, about 30 more minutes.'),
(1267, 201, 1, 'Preheat oven to 375°F and line baking sheets with parchment paper.In a large bowl, whisk together 1 cup granulated sugar, oil, eggs, and molasses.and vanilla.In a separate mixing bowl, whisk together the flours and starches, xanthan gum, baking soda, spices, and salt.'),
(1268, 208, 2, 'Whisk in the yogurt, bananas, maple syrup, sugar (if using), and vanilla, mixing until smooth.Stir in the oats, baking soda, and cinnamon. Finally, spoon in the flour and gently stir it in until just combined. If you\'re adding any mix-ins, fold them in now.'),
(1269, 203, 5, 'Transfer tofu to paper towel-lined plate to drain.'),
(1270, 200, 12, 'Transfer pan to a wire rack to cool.'),
(1271, 201, 2, 'Mix the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients, and stir until fully combined.'),
(1272, 208, 3, 'Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan, spreading it out evenly.'),
(1273, 203, 6, '2'),
(1274, 203, 7, 'Return the wok to high heat and add the mushrooms. Cook, stirring and tossing occasionally, until mushrooms release their liquid and start to brown, about 4 minutes.'),
(1275, 200, 13, 'Serve with whipped cream, if desired.'),
(1276, 201, 3, 'Roll 1 teaspoon of dough into a ball, and roll in the remaining sugar to coat.'),
(1277, 208, 4, 'Bake for 35-40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.'),
(1278, 203, 8, 'Add the garlic and chiles and cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, about fifteen seconds.'),
(1279, 201, 4, 'Place on prepared baking sheet, leaving 2-inches between cookies.'),
(1280, 208, 5, 'Remove the bread from the oven and let it cool in the pan for about 10 minutes before transferring it to a cooling rack to cool completely.'),
(1281, 203, 9, 'Add the fermented black beans, and stir-fry until they are hot, about 30 seconds.'),
(1282, 201, 5, 'Bake in preheated oven for 8-10 minutes. Allow cookies to remain on cookie sheet for 2 minutes before transferring them to a cooling rack to cool completely. Once cooled, store cookies in an airtight container.'),
(1283, 203, 10, 'Add the broth and soy sauce.'),
(1284, 203, 11, '3'),
(1285, 203, 12, 'When mixture comes to a simmer, reduce heat to medium, add the spinach, and cook until it wilts, about 15 seconds. Season to taste with salt, if necessary. Stir in the cornstarch and water mixture, and cook until the liquid thickens.'),
(1286, 203, 13, 'Add the scallions, stir well, and then remove from heat.'),
(1287, 203, 14, 'Add the chili oil.'),
(1288, 203, 15, 'Serve immediately with rice.'),
(1289, 209, 1, 'Fill a saucepan with water and bring to the boil.'),
(1290, 209, 2, 'Add the broad beans and return to the boil. Cook for one minute then drain in a colander under running water until cold.'),
(1291, 209, 3, 'Remove the beans from their skins and set aside.'),
(1292, 210, 1, 'Heat 1 tablespoon peanut oil in a preheated wok and stir-fry onion until translucent. Toss in garlic, ginger, and mushrooms and stir-fry for another minute.'),
(1293, 209, 4, 'Mix the mint with two tablespoons of the olive oil and set aside.'),
(1294, 210, 2, 'Add oyster sauce and 2 tablespoons soy sauce and cook for another 30 seconds.'),
(1295, 209, 5, 'Melt 25g/1oz of the butter with the remaining oil in a large non-stick saucepan and fry the onion and garlic for five minutes until softened, but not coloured. Stir in the thyme, lemon zest, bay leaf and risotto rice and cook for a few seconds more until the rice is glistening.'),
(1296, 210, 3, 'Remove wok contents to a bowl and set aside.'),
(1297, 209, 6, 'Pour the wine in to the pan and boil over a medium heat until the liquid has reduced by half. Slowly start adding the stock, a ladleful at a time, stirring well between each addition. Simmer for 2-3 minutes or until the liquid has almost all been absorbed before adding more. Cook for 15 minutes or until the rice is tender.'),
(1298, 210, 4, 'Heat 2 tablespoons peanut oil in the hot wok and stir-fry cabbage, bell peppers, bamboo shoots, and carrot for 3 minutes. Toss in bean sprouts, sugar,  cup reserved mushroom water, salt, and pepper and cook for 1 minute.'),
(1299, 209, 7, 'Meanwhile, fill a medium saucepan with water and bring to the boil. Cook the runner beans for three minutes, or until tender.');
INSERT INTO `Instruction` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `step_num`, `instruction`) VALUES
(1300, 210, 5, 'Add onion and mushroom mixture, rice wine, and sesame oil and stir to combine well.Cook noodles in plenty of water at a rolling boil for about a minute.'),
(1301, 209, 8, 'Drain in a colander then return to the pan and toss with a small knob of the remaining butter and plenty of ground black pepper.'),
(1302, 210, 6, 'Drain thoroughly, rinse under cold running water, and drain again. Toss noodles with remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce and remaining 1 teaspoon peanut oil.To serve, place noodles on a large warmed serving platter, spoon vegetable mixture on top, and mix lightly.'),
(1303, 209, 9, 'Remove the thyme and lemon zest from the rice and discard. Stir in the broad beans, peas and asparagus with the remaining stock and cook for three minutes until tender, stirring regularly.'),
(1304, 210, 7, 'Garnish with green onions sprinkled over the top.'),
(1305, 209, 10, 'Remove from the heat and stir in the feta. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cover with a lid and set aside.'),
