(1891, 305, 8, 'Remove the lid and continue to simmer for an additional 20 minutes or until all liquid is evaporated. Fluff with a fork and serve.'),
(1892, 307, 5, 'Start the processor and slowly add the oil from the top of the processor'),
(1893, 304, 8, 'Add the lamb shanks and squash; simmer just until warmed through.'),
(1894, 307, 6, 'Blend until all the items until the sauce is smooth.  Personally, I like to stop a few notches before they turn completely smooth.  I like the roughness of the pesto sauce.In medium pan, heat up the sunflower oil'),
(1895, 304, 9, 'Add the cannellini beans, cover and remove from heat.'),
(1896, 307, 7, 'Add cooked spaghetti and the pesto sauce'),
(1897, 304, 10, 'Let stand for a few minutes to allow for the flavors to blend.8 Spoon the vegetables and sauce into large shallow bowls and set the lamb shanks on top.'),
(1898, 307, 8, 'Heat on medium heat for about 5 minutes or until all the spaghetti is well coated'),
(1899, 304, 11, 'Garnish with the gremolata and serve.'),
(1900, 307, 9, 'Remove from heat and move to serving dish'),
(1901, 307, 10, 'Chop the remaining 2 basil leaves'),
(1902, 307, 11, 'Garnish with the chopped basil leaves and shredded Parmesan cheese'),
(1903, 311, 1, 'Set your Instant Pot to Saut and saut the diced bacon until it just begins to crisp around the edges and some of the fat has melted.'),
(1904, 311, 2, 'Add the butternut squash, cranberries, chopped rosemary and saute until the squash is golden on the edges and the bacon is crisp.Meanwhile butterfly your turkey tenderloins by gently slicing them lengthwise ALMOST all the way through, leaving the edge attached. Open each tenderloin up like a butterfly.Once the filling is done, gently spoon it into the center of each turkey tenderloin. Fold the tenderloin back up and seal the edge by weaving a rosemary sprig through the open edge, or tying the tenderloin with cooking twine.With your Instant Pot still on Saut sear each side of the tenderloins for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until golden.'),
(1905, 314, 1, 'In a small bowl, combine the brown sugar, basil, salt and chili powder. Gradually stir in 1 tablespoon oil until crumbly. Rub over both sides of pork chops.'),
(1906, 311, 3, 'Remove the tenderloins from the instant pot to make room for the rice.'),
(1907, 310, 1, 'Add all ingredients except macaroni to a crock pot and simmer for 6 hours. About 30 minutes before serving cook the pasta and add it to the simmering chili. Allow flavors to blend another 30 minutes or so.'),
(1908, 309, 1, 'Preheat oven to 180C.'),
(1909, 314, 2, 'In a large skillet, cook pork in remaining oil over medium heat for 7-8 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.'),
(1910, 311, 4, 'Add the rice to your instant pot and saut for 1-2 minutes, just until it starts to smell nutty.'),
(1911, 311, 5, 'Add the white wine and stir to deglaze.'),
(1912, 309, 2, 'Melt chocolate chips in a heat safe bowl over boiling water and let it cool down.'),
(1913, 312, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350 F. Generously grease a 1 dozen muffin tin.In a large bowl, combine the almond flour, tapioca flour, baking soda and coconut sugar. In a separate mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, melted ghee and vanilla. Stir the wet ingredients into the almond flour mixture, beating lightly by hand with a wooden spoon, until thoroughly combined. Gently fold in the raspberries and chocolate.Divide the batter equally between the 12 greased muffin cups.'),
(1914, 311, 6, 'Add enough water or chicken broth to your instant pot to cook the rice (for me it was 3 1/2 cups since I already added the 1/2 cup of wine, but double check your Instant Pot Rice instructions.) Replace the tenderloins on top of the rice.'),
(1915, 313, 1, 'For the crust:Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line an 8x8-inch baking pan with foil.'),
(1916, 309, 3, 'Mix sugar and butter with an electric mixer until its crumbly.'),
(1917, 312, 2, 'Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.Allow the muffins to cool for 5 minutes before removing from the pan.'),
(1918, 311, 7, 'Add the whole rosemary sprigs, if desired.Seal your Instant Pot and cook on Rice.Once finished cooking let the pressure come down naturally for at least 10 minutes before releasing the pressure valve.'),
(1919, 313, 2, 'Place the graham crackers, sugar, and salt in the bowl of a food processor and pulse until finely ground.'),
(1920, 309, 4, 'Add in mashed bananas and mix well.'),
(1921, 312, 3, 'Serve warm or at room temperature.Nutrition (per serving): 201 calories, 13.7g total fat, 56.9mg cholesterol, 72.7mg sodium, 179.8mg potassium, 14.9g carbohydrates, 3.6g fiber, 5.6g sugar, 2.5g protein.'),
(1922, 308, 1, 'Stir kefir, honey, and salt in a small bowl; cover and chill.Toast seeds in a dry small skillet over medium-high, tossing occasionally, until fragrant and coriander seeds start to pop, about 3 minutes.'),
(1923, 311, 8, 'Remove the rosemary sprigs. Slice the tenderloin and serve it over the rice.'),
(1924, 313, 3, 'Add the melted butter and pulse until the mixture is moistened. Press the mixture into the bottom of the prepared baking pan.'),
(1925, 309, 5, 'Add eggs, one each time and mix.'),
(1926, 308, 2, 'Let cool; finely grind in a spice mill.Pure spice mix, watercress, broth, and salt in a blender until smooth. Cover and chill until ready to use.Toast caraway in a dry large skillet over medium-high, tossing, until fragrant, about 30 seconds.'),
(1927, 313, 4, 'Bake for 10 minutes.'),
(1928, 309, 6, 'Stir in yogurt and mix until combined well.'),
(1929, 308, 3, 'Let cool; finely grind in spice mill.Cook scallions in same skillet, turning occasionally, until charred, 5 minutes.'),
(1930, 313, 5, 'Remove to a cooling rack and let cool completely.For the filling:In a small saucepan set over medium-low heat, combine the chocolate chips and condensed milk.'),
(1931, 309, 7, 'Mix flour, cinnamon and baking soda in a seperate bowl and combine it with the wet ingredients.'),
(1932, 308, 4, 'Let cool, then coarsely chop. Reserve skillet.Process caraway, scallions, chile, garlic, bread, ricotta, lentils, broth, onion powder, paprika, and 1 tsp. salt in a food processor to a paste (some larger pieces of lentils should still be visible). Form into 12 balls.'),
(1933, 313, 6, 'Heat until the mixture is melted, thick, and smooth, stirring constantly.'),
(1934, 309, 8, 'Take 1 cup of the batter and mix it with melted chocolate.'),
(1935, 316, 1, 'Combine the puréed fruit, ¼ cup sugar and lemon juice in a large bowl.'),
(1936, 308, 5, 'Pour oil into a large heavy skillet to  a depth of \" and heat over medium-high until oil bubbles immediately when a pinch of lentil mixture is added. Working in batches if needed, cook croquettes until deep golden brown and crisp, about 2 minutes per side.'),
(1937, 313, 7, 'Pour over graham cracker crust.'),
(1938, 309, 9, 'Line your pan with parchment paper and spoon the two batters alternately into it.'),
(1939, 316, 2, 'Add the yogurt and stir until well combined. A whisk works very well for this. Chill for a few hours before churning in your ice cream maker.Meanwhile, stir together the diced fruit and 1 teaspoon sugar and chill until ready to use.When you\'re ready for the ice cream maker, stir the vodka into the dice fruit and set aside.'),
(1940, 308, 6, 'Drain on paper towels; season with salt. Swirl both sauces in bowls; top with croquettes.'),
(1941, 313, 8, 'Place in the refrigerator while making the marshmallow topping.For the marshmallow topping:In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the whisk attachment, beat the egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.Meanwhile, in a small saucepan set over medium-high heat, combine the sugar, corn syrup, water, and salt. Bring the mixture to a boil and continue to cook until a candy thermometer registers exactly 240°F. Immediately remove from heat. Turn the mixture on low speed and carefully and gradually drizzle the syrup into the egg whites. Increase speed to medium-high and beat until the mixture is thick and glossy and looks like marshmallow fluff, about 7 minutes longer.'),
(1942, 309, 10, 'Swirl gently using a fork or a knife, but dont over-swirl.'),
(1943, 316, 3, 'Transfer the yogurt mixture to the bowl of your ice cream maker and process according to manufacturer\'s directions. About halfway through add the diced fruit while the machine is still on and continue to churn. I added the fruit about 15 minutes into the process and continued to churn for another 15 minutes.Turn off the ice cream machine, transfer the frozen yogurt to a container and freeze for a few hours to let it firm up.'),
(1944, 308, 7, 'Drizzle with pomegranate molasses and finish with watercress.Do Ahead: Croquettes can be formed 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Bring to room temperature before frying.'),
(1945, 313, 9, 'Add in the vanilla and beat until combined.'),
(1946, 309, 11, 'Bake it for 50-55 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out with little crumbs and cool completely.'),
(1947, 313, 10, 'Spread the marshmallow topping evenly over the chocolate fudge layer. Use a kitchen torch to gently torch the marshmallow layer until lightly golden. Alternatively, place the pan under the broiler and broil for 1 minute, or until lightly golden.Refrigerate the pan for at least 1 hour before cutting into squares and serving. The squares can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.'),
(1948, 309, 12, 'For the ganache, put chocolate chips in a heat proof bowl.'),
(1949, 309, 13, 'Heat heavy cream in a small saucepan until it boils and pour it over chocolate. (See the video above)'),
(1950, 309, 14, 'Pour over the completely cooled banana bread and wait for about half an hour before serving.'),
(1951, 315, 1, 'Combine garlic, ginger, turmeric, garam masala, coriander, and cumin in a small bowl.'),
(1952, 315, 2, 'Whisk yogurt, salt, and half of spice mixture in a medium bowl; add chicken and turn to coat. Cover and chill 4-6 hours. Cover and chill remaining spice mixture.'),
(1953, 315, 3, 'Heat ghee in a large heavy pot over medium heat.'),
(1954, 317, 1, 'Whisk marinade / dressing ingredients together to combine.'),
(1955, 315, 4, 'Add onion, tomato paste, cardamom, and chiles and cook, stirring often, until tomato paste has darkened and onion is soft, about 5 minutes.'),
(1956, 317, 2, 'Pour half the marinade into a shallow dish to marinade the chicken fillets for two hours if time allows. Refrigerate the reserved untouched marinade to use as a dressing.'),
(1957, 315, 5, 'Add remaining half of spice mixture and cook, stirring often, until bottom of pot begins  to brown, about 4 minutes.'),
(1958, 317, 3, 'Heat a nonstick pan (or grill pan or skillet) over medium heat with about a teaspoon of oil and sear / grill chicken fillets on each side until golden, crispy and cooked through. (Grill in batches to prevent excess water being released.) Once chicken is cooked, set aside and allow to rest.Wipe pan over with paper towel; drizzle with another teaspoon of oil and fry the bacon until crispy.Slice chicken into strips and prepare salad with leaves, tomatoes, avocado slices, corn, onion strips and chicken.'),
(1959, 315, 6, 'Add tomatoes with juices, crushing them with your hands as you add them. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer, stirring often and scraping up browned bits from bottom  of pot, until sauce thickens, 8-10 minutes.'),
(1960, 317, 4, 'Whisk 2 tablespoons of water into the remaining untouched marinade / dressing and drizzle over the salad. Sprinkle the bacon over the top and season with a little extra salt and cracked pepper (optional).'),
(1961, 315, 7, 'Add cream and chopped cilantro. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens, 30-40 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat broiler. Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil and set a wire rack inside sheet. Arrange chicken on rack in a single layer. Broil until chicken starts to blacken in spots (it will not be cooked through), about 10 minutes.'),
(1962, 318, 1, 'Using a mixer, beat butter, vanilla, egg, and cream cheese until fluffy.'),
(1963, 315, 8, 'Cut chicken into bite-size pieces, add to sauce, and simmer, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through, 8-10 minutes.'),
(1964, 318, 2, 'Add the cake mix.'),
(1965, 315, 9, 'Serve with rice and cilantro sprigs.DO AHEAD: Chicken can be made 2 days ahead. Cover; chill. Reheat before serving.'),
(1966, 318, 3, 'Chill batter for 30 minutes.'),
(1967, 318, 4, 'Scoop dough into balls and dip in a bowl of powdered sugar.'),
(1968, 318, 5, 'Bake at 350 for 9-11 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Sift powdered sugar on top.'),
(1969, 321, 1, 'Place egg, parmesan, breadcrumbs, garlic, seasoning, Worcestershire, salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Finely grate the onion into the mixture. Stir it together until it forms a thick paste.'),
(1970, 322, 1, 'In a medium sized bowl whisk together 1 cup cold milk, cornstarch, kosher salt, vanilla bean paste and egg yolks, set aside. In a medium sized pot add remaining 3 cups cold milk, butter and sugar.'),
(1971, 321, 2, 'Add the turkey to the bowl and work the mixture together gently. You dont want to over mix the meatball mixture, but make sure that the turkey and seasonings are all mixed through.'),
(1972, 320, 1, 'To Make the Broth'),
(1973, 322, 2, 'Whisk constantly until the mixture is scalding.'),
(1974, 321, 3, 'Heat a large skillet over medium high heat.'),
(1975, 319, 1, 'Preheat oven to 400F. Coat a 9-by-13-inch baking dish (or similar gratin dish) with cooking spray.'),
(1976, 321, 4, 'Add the oil to the pan and let it heat through.Scoop desired size meatballs in uniform size.'),
(1977, 320, 2, 'In a large saucepan, combine the oil, onion, and garlic and sweat over medium heat until translucent.'),
(1978, 319, 2, 'Place garlic, basil and thyme on your chopping board; mince well.'),
(1979, 322, 3, 'Whisk in milk/cornstarch mixture and cook over medium heat until thickened. You do not want the mixture to boil but you want to make sure it\'s thickening up nicely.'),
(1980, 321, 5, 'Place meatballs into the hot pan. Once you put them down, dont move them.Cook meatballs about 3-5 minutes per side, or until theyre browned. At this point you can do two different things with your meatballs:Oven: preheat oven to 350F.'),
(1981, 320, 3, 'Add the chipotle and habanero chiles and sauté for 2 minutes more.'),
(1982, 327, 1, 'Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Have all ingredients at room temperature.Melt the 5 ounces of the chocolate in a double boiler over hot water.'),
(1983, 319, 3, 'Spread half the breadcrumbs evenly in the prepared baking dish. Strew onion over the breadcrumbs. Distribute half the diced tomato over the onion, then sprinkle with half the garlic-herb mixture. Sprinkle with vinegar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.'),
(1984, 322, 4, 'Remove the pudding from the heat and stir every 10 minutes. The mixture should start to thicken a little more off the heat. While the pudding is cooling make your peanut butter nuggets. In the bowl of an electric mixer add powdered sugar and peanut butter.'),
(1985, 320, 4, 'Add the chicken stock, bring to a simmer, add the epazote, and simmer for 30 minutes; season to taste with salt and pepper; strain and reserve.To Make the Eggs');
INSERT INTO `Instruction` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `step_num`, `instruction`) VALUES
(1986, 327, 2, 'Remove from heat and let cool.Separate the eggs. Cream the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.  Beat the egg yolks in gradually until light in color.'),
(1987, 319, 4, 'Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
(1988, 322, 5, 'Mix on medium speed until small peanut butter nuggets start to come together. If the mixture is too sandy simply add a few drops of water to the mixture and larger nuggets will form. After pudding is somewhat cool you can start to assemble the pie.'),
(1989, 324, 1, 'Preheat the oven at 375 degrees F.'),
(1990, 320, 5, 'Sauté the chorizo in a small skillet over medium-high heat until browned and separated into small pieces.'),
(1991, 327, 3, 'Add the melted, cooled chocolate and beat it in. Gradually add the sifted flour to the batter.Beat the egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold them into the mixture.'),
(1992, 319, 5, 'Add a third of the zucchini; you want it to saut, not stew, so don\'t crowd it. Saut, turning the pieces once, until golden and not quite tender, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes per side. When the slices are done, use a fork to transfer them to the gratin, overlapping the slices. Cook the remaining zucchini in two batches, each time using 2 teaspoons oil. Strew the remaining tomatoes and garlic-herb mixture over the zucchini. Season with the remaining 1/8 teaspoon salt and a grinding of pepper. Toss the remaining 1 cup breadcrumbs with the remaining 1 tablespoon oil and sprinkle over the gratin.'),
(1993, 322, 6, 'Add half the peanut butter nuggets to the bottom of the pie shell. Top with pudding.'),
(1994, 324, 2, 'Heat a skillet on medium heat and add the sausage.   While cooking the sausage break it up in small pieces with a spoon or spatula.  When the sausage is done cooking remove it from the pan on to a paper towel and set aside.  Shred the cheese and set aside.In a medium size bowl, add the eggs, pepper, and milk.'),
(1995, 320, 6, 'Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.'),
(1996, 325, 1, '1 Break thick shells (lobster and crab) into smaller pieces by putting in a sealed, thick plastic bag and either rolling with a rolling pin or hitting with a meat hammer to crush.'),
(1997, 327, 4, 'Pour batter into one ungreased 9 inch springform pan.'),
(1998, 319, 6, 'Bake the gratin until bubbly hot, 20 to 25 minutes.'),
(1999, 322, 7, 'Add half the remaining peanut butter nuggets to the top of the pudding. Top with whipped cream and remaining peanut butter nuggets.'),
(2000, 324, 3, 'Whisk together.'),
(2001, 320, 7, 'Add enough vegetable oil to the skillet to make about 2 teaspoons and heat until hot. Stir in the onions and garlic and sauté until soft; add the serrano chiles and chorizo.'),
(2002, 325, 2, 'Cut up thinner shrimp shells with a chef\'s knife. Don\'t crush or cut too small. You can even skip this step if you want, if you are already dealing with broken up shell pieces (like cracked crab).'),
(2003, 327, 5, 'Bake at 325 degrees F (165 degrees C) for 50 to 60 minutes. Allow cake to cool completely before removing from pan and icing. Once cool remove from pan and slice cake horizontally.  Set top half aside and spread filling of pureed jam between the layers. Cover top and sides with warm Sachertorte icing.To Make Sachertorte Icing: Melt 1 tablespoon butter and 4 ounces chocolate in a double boiler over hot water.'),
(2004, 319, 7, 'Remove from the oven and immediately sprinkle with Parmesan.'),
(2005, 322, 8, 'Let the pie cool in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours to set up before cutting.'),
(2006, 324, 4, 'Heat a skillet on medium heat and add ½ tablespoon of butter.  As it’s melting pour in the eggs and stir as they cook.  When the eggs are scrambled, remove them from the heat and set aside for just a moment.Grease a cookie sheet with about ½ tablespoon of butter.  Lay two of the tortillas on the cookie sheet.'),
(2007, 328, 1, 'Presoak the cashews for 2 hours in cold water as well as the raisins for the base for 3o minutes.'),
(2008, 320, 8, 'Pour the broth into the saucepan and bring to a simmer; drop in the eggs and poach until just set.'),
(2009, 325, 3, 'Place in a large roasting pan and roast at 400°F for 10 minutes (this step you can skip, but it greatly enhances the flavor).'),
(2010, 327, 6, 'Add the coffee and beat well.  Sift and add the confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.'),
(2011, 324, 5, 'Add a layer of shredded cheese on each tortilla reserving half of the quantity of cheese for later.  Next, add a layer of cooked sausage, scrambled eggs, and salsa to the tortillas.'),
(2012, 328, 2, 'Drain and set aside.Line a 9-by-5-inch loaf baking pan with parchment paper and set aside.In your food processor add the base ingredients and pulse until combined, about 30 seconds.'),
(2013, 320, 9, 'Add the bread and epazote and simmer for 1 minute more.In each of 4 soup bowls, serve 2 eggs along with a large ladle of the broth.'),
(2014, 328, 3, 'Transfer the mixture to the prepared loaf baking pan with a spatula.'),
(2015, 327, 7, 'Spread the warm icing on the top and sides of the torte'),
(2016, 320, 10, 'Garnish with chopped hard cooked egg and serve.'),
(2017, 323, 1, 'Save Recipe'),
(2018, 325, 4, 'Put the shells in a large stock pot and add enough water to cover the shells with an inch of water. 2'),
(2019, 328, 4, 'Place the cheesecake layer in your food processor and pulse until smooth, about 2-3 minutes depending on your food processor. Evenly spread this mixture over the base layer.In a small bowl mix the topping ingredients. Distribute the topping over the cheesecake layer and with your hands press down lightly.'),
(2020, 328, 5, 'Place the cheesecake in the freezer for at least 3-4 hours.Thaw cheesecake for 15-20 minutes before serving. At this time you can cut cheesecake into 2-3 inch. Store leftover cheesecake covered in the freezer.'),
(2021, 325, 5, 'Put the stove temperature on medium high and slowly heat the shells in the water. As soon as you see that little bubbles are starting to come up to the surface, reduce the heat to medium. Do not let it boil. You want to maintain the temperature at just below a simmer, where the bubbles just occasionally come up to the surface. Do not stir the shells. Stirring will muddy up the stock. As the bubbles come up to the surface a film of foam will develop on the surface. Use a large slotted spoon to skim away this foam.'),
(2022, 325, 6, 'Let the shells cook like this for about an hour; skim the foam every few minutes. The foam comes from shells releasing impurities as their temperature increases.3'),
(2023, 323, 2, 'Print Recipe'),
(2024, 324, 6, 'Add the remaining shredded cheese.  Top each quesadilla with a tortilla.In a small bowl, melt the remaining butter, and brush it on top of the tortilla.'),
(2025, 325, 7, 'Put the thyme, bay leaves, and parsley in cheese cloth. Secure with kitchen string to make a bouquet garni.4 Once the stock has stopped releasing foam, you can add the wine, onions, carrots, celery, tomato paste, herb bouquet garni, and peppercorns. Bring to a low simmer and reduce heat so that the stock continues to simmer, but not boil, for 30 minutes. If more foam comes to the surface, skim it off.'),
(2026, 323, 3, 'Slow Cooker Lentil Cauliflower Stew'),
(2027, 324, 7, 'Bake in a preheated oven until the cheese melts and the outside edges of the tortillas turn a light golden color (about 15 to 18 minutes).'),
(2028, 325, 8, 'Add salt and remove from heat. 5 Dampen a few layers of cheesecloth and place over a large, fine mesh strainer, over a large pot or bowl.'),
(2029, 324, 8, 'Cut each quesadilla into quarters with a knife or pizza cutter.'),
(2030, 323, 4, 'Ingredients16 oz dried lentils1 tbsp olive oil1 large onion, chopped (about 2 cups of onion)2 garlic cloves, chopped1 lb. cauliflower, chopped into very small florets2 leeks, white and green parts only, halved, washed carefully, and chopped)2 large carrots, peeled and chopped3 celery stalks, chopped2 bay leaves1 tbsp chopped fresh thyme or 1 tsp dried thyme2 tsp kosher salt (or to taste)1 tsp cumin1/2 tsp cayenne (very spicy-- add 1/4 tsp or less for a milder flavor)1/4 tsp black pepper8 cups low sodium vegetable broth1 large can (32 oz) diced tomatoes with juice2 cups chopped kale or Swiss chard'),
(2031, 324, 9, 'Serve hot with your favorite salsa.  Store any leftovers in the refrigerator and warm them up in the oven or in a toaster oven.'),
(2032, 325, 9, 'Pour the stock into the strainer. Discard the solids. Either use the stock right away, or cool for future use. If you aren\'t going to use in a couple of days, freeze (remember to leave some head room at the top of your freezer container for the liquid to expand as it freezes.)'),
(2033, 323, 5, 'Optional Toppings'),
(2034, 326, 1, 'Place a rack in the center of the oven and heat oven to 350 F. Grease a 10-inch springform cake pan.In a medium bowl, whisk together flours, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and cardamom. Set aside.In a small bowl, whisk together maple syrup, eggs, coconut cream, coconut oil, vanilla and almond extract.'),
(2035, 323, 6, 'Plain yogurt, herbed goat cheese, feta, crème fraîche, grated Parmesan, Greek yogurt or lowfat sour cream'),
(2036, 326, 2, 'Add the coconut cream mixture all at once to the dry ingredients. Stir until just combined and no lumps remain. Spoon batter into the prepared pan. Top batter with fresh raspberries {you may have some extra berries left over}, gently pressing into the batter. Sprinkle with sliced almonds and then sprinkle generously with coconut sugar.'),
(2037, 323, 7, 'Prep Time: 15 Minutes'),
(2038, 326, 3, 'Bake for 40-45 minutes, or until a skewer inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean. Allow cake to cool to room temperature before slicing to serve.Top with any remaining berries.Cake will last well wrapped in the refrigerator, for up to 3 days.'),
(2039, 323, 8, 'Cook Time: 90 - 8 Hours'),
(2040, 323, 9, 'Total Time: 105 - 8 Hours 15 Minutes'),
(2041, 323, 10, 'Servings: 8-10'),
(2042, 323, 11, 'Kosher Key: Pareve (or Dairy with optional add-ins)'),
(2043, 329, 1, 'Rinse, drain and thoroughly dry jackfruit. Chop off the center \"core\" portion of the fruit and discard.'),
(2044, 329, 2, 'Place in a mixing bowl and set aside.'),
(2045, 329, 3, 'Mix together BBQ seasoning and add to jackfruit. Toss to coat.'),
(2046, 329, 4, 'Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add 1-2 Tbsp oil of choice and seasoned jackfruit. Toss to coat and cook for 2-3 minutes to achieve some color.'),
(2047, 329, 5, 'Add BBQ sauce and thin with enough water to make a sauce. Stir and reduce heat to low- medium and cook for about 20 minutes (up to 35 minutes on low for a deeper flavor).'),
(2048, 329, 6, 'Remove lid and stir occasionally. TIP: For finer texture, use two forks to shred the jackfruit as it cooks down.In the meantime, make slaw by adding all ingredients except vegetables (avocado through salt + pepper) to a small mixing bowl and whisk to combine. Thin with water until a thick sauce is made, then add veggies and toss to coat. Set in the refrigerator until serving.Once the jackfruit has been properly simmered, turn up heat to medium-high and cook for 2-3 more minutes to get a little extra color/texture (a tip I learned from Namely Marly!). Then remove from heat.'),
(2049, 329, 7, 'Place generous portions of slaw on the bottom buns, top with generous serving of BBQ jackfruit, and cashews.'),
(2050, 329, 8, 'Serve with extra BBQ sauce!Leftover jackfruit keeps for up to a couple days in the fridge, though best when fresh.'),
(2051, 333, 1, 'Place egg in a saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring water to a boil and immediately remove from heat. Cover and let eggs stand in hot water for 10 to 12 minutes.'),
(2052, 333, 2, 'Remove from hot water, cool, peel and chop.'),
(2053, 333, 3, 'Place the chopped eggs in a bowl, and stir in the mayonnaise, mustard and green onion. Season with salt, pepper and paprika. Stir and serve on your favorite bread or crackers.'),
(2054, 338, 1, 'In the bowl of a food processor, combine the olives and giardiniera. Pulse until pieces are approximately 1/4 inch in size.'),
(2055, 338, 2, 'Transfer the olive mixture to a bowl. Stir in the red wine vinegar and olive oil. Set aside. (Olive salad can be made up to 24 hours in advance.)'),
(2056, 338, 3, 'Split the bread in half lengthwise and spread the cut sides with the olive mixture.'),
(2057, 338, 4, 'Layer the soppressata on the bottom half of the roll followed by the capicola, then salami, the mortadella and provolone. Arrange the arugula and the peppers on top of the provolone.'),
(2058, 338, 5, 'Place the top of the roll on the sandwich and wrap tightly with plastic wrap.'),
(2059, 338, 6, 'Transfer the sandwich to the refrigerator and allow to rest for 1 hour or overnight.'),
(2060, 338, 7, 'To serve, cut the sandwich into 4 equal wedges.'),
(2061, 334, 1, 'In a Dutch oven, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.'),
(2062, 335, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line a cookie sheet with foil and top with a cookie rack sprayed with cooking spray.'),
(2063, 334, 2, 'Add the eggplant, zucchini, onion, yellow pepper and garlic; cook until tender.'),
(2064, 330, 1, 'In a medium-sized mixing bowl, mix the cream cheese and butter until light and fluffy (about three minutes on high speed).'),
(2065, 335, 2, 'Combine panko, pecans, thyme and salt on a plate.'),
(2066, 334, 3, 'Add tomatoes, rice, 1/2 cup of cheese, broth and seasonings; mix well.'),
(2067, 331, 1, 'Place oven rack on the lowest position in oven and preheat to 450 degrees'),
(2068, 332, 1, 'Bring carrots, broth, tomatoes with juice, and 2 cups water to a simmer in large stockpot with steamer insert over medium heat.'),
(2069, 330, 2, 'Mix in the sugar, salt, and vanilla.'),
(2070, 335, 3, 'Combine yogurt, water, lemon and lemon zest in a larger bowl.Dredge chicken tenders in yogurt and shake off excess. Press into panko and place on cookie rack.'),
(2071, 334, 4, 'Transfer to a greased 13-in. x 9-in. baking dish. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.'),
(2072, 331, 2, 'Pour black beans into a saucepan with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste'),
(2073, 332, 2, 'Place kale, whole basil leaves, and whole chives in steamer insert. Set steamer inside stockpot, cover, and steam 5 to 7 minutes, using tongs to stir halfway through.'),
(2074, 335, 4, 'Bake for 15 - 20 minutes until chicken is cooked through.If you\'d like a more browned tender, turn on the broiler for the last minute or two.'),
(2075, 334, 5, 'Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.'),
(2076, 330, 3, 'Mix in the flour until just combined.'),
(2077, 331, 3, 'Heat the beans over medium-low while using a potato masher to mash the beans to desired texture (you could also use a can of organic refried beans if you would like)Oil the bottom of an iron skillet with olive oil'),
(2078, 332, 3, 'Remove and discard basil and chives.'),
(2079, 330, 4, 'Place the dough on a floured board and form it into a ball.Divide into two roughly equal pieces, wrap each in plastic, and refrigerate for at least one hour.In a small saucepan on medium heat, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.Reduce heat to low and cook for another ten minutes, stirring frequently.  The mixture should thicken considerably.'),
(2080, 331, 4, 'Spread the pizza dough to desired thickness on the bottom and sides of skillet'),
(2081, 332, 4, 'Add kale, beans, and vinegar to soup, and return to a simmer. Season with salt and pepper, if desired. Stir in chopped basil and chives just before serving.'),
(2082, 330, 5, 'Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.'),
(2083, 331, 5, 'Spread a layer of refried beans on the pizza crust'),
(2084, 339, 1, 'In large pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.'),
(2085, 330, 6, 'Remove one of the wrapped sections of dough from the refrigerator.'),
(2086, 331, 6, 'Sprinkle on a layer of shredded cheese and taco meat'),
(2087, 339, 2, 'Add garlic, green pepper and onion; cook 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are softened, stirring occasionally.Stir in black pepper, salt and red pepper flakes; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in crushed tomatoes and broth; heat to boiling over medium-high heat.Stir in turkey and gnocchi; cook 3 minutes or until gnocchi float to surface.'),
(2088, 336, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.'),
(2089, 330, 7, 'Roll out to a roughly 10\" square. The dough is sticky, so be sure to flour your surface and your rolling pin really well.'),
(2090, 331, 7, 'Place the skillet in the oven and bake for 9 to 12 minutes or until crust is slightly browned'),
(2091, 339, 3, 'Serve garnished with cheese.'),
(2092, 336, 2, 'Place the chicken on a baking sheet and rub with the olive oil, chili powder, cumin, and paprika. Season with salt and pepper.'),
(2093, 340, 1, 'Cut mangos into small cubes. The easiest way to cut mangos is buy peeling it with a potato peeler and then cutting it into pieces. Put mango into a blender, with lemon juice.Blend until it is a smooth purée. Mango puree can stay refrigerated for several days in a fridge.'),
(2094, 330, 8, 'Cut the rolled dough into 25 2\" squares.'),
(2095, 331, 8, 'Carefully remove the skillet from your oven'),
(2096, 336, 3, 'Add the poblano to the baking sheet.'),
(2097, 340, 2, 'Place a few table spoons of mango puree, mint leaves and fill it with club soda. Optionally, you can add some ice to it.'),
(2098, 330, 9, 'Place approximately one teaspoon of cherry pie filling in the center of each square.Fold the squares diagonally to create little triangles and use a fork to crimp the edges of the triangle.'),
(2099, 331, 9, 'Top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes, avocado and other toppings as desired'),
(2100, 336, 4, 'Transfer to the oven and bake for 20 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through. Shred the chicken with two forks. De-seed the poblano and cut into slices.'),
(2101, 330, 10, 'Cut a tiny slice in the top of each triangle.  This lets the steam out during baking and also makes the turnovers look pretty because there will be a little cherry filling peeking through the top.'),
(2102, 341, 1, 'For the cake, whisk together the egg whites, and 1/4 cup of the milk in small bowl until slightly combined. Set aside.In mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar for 2 minutes on medium.'),
(2103, 341, 2, 'Add in dry ingredients and mix until combined. Slowly in a steady stream add in the egg white mixture. Beat in remaining milk and melted white chocolate bar.Fill cupcake liners half full with batter and bake in a 350 degree oven for about 15 minutes.'),
(2104, 336, 5, 'Add the shredded chicken and poblano to a bowl.'),
(2105, 330, 11, 'Place the turnovers on a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper or a Silpat.Repeat for the other section of dough.Chill the formed turnover cookies for about 10 minutes in the freezer to help them hold their shape during baking.Preheat oven to 350 F.'),
(2106, 341, 3, 'Remove and cool in pan 5 minutes then transfer to a wire rack. Cool completely before frosting.For the frosting, beat butter 5 minutes until it becomes pale in color.'),
(2107, 336, 6, 'Add 1/2 cup salsa verde, the rice and the cilantro, toss to combine.'),
(2108, 330, 12, 'Remove cookie sheets from the freezer.'),
(2109, 341, 4, 'Add sugar, melted white chocolate and whole milk. Beat an additional 5 minutes until fluffy. Fill a disposable pastry bag with frosting (no tip on the end). Set aside.For PB frosing, beat butter 5 minutes until pale in color.'),
(2110, 336, 7, 'Pour 1/2 cup of the salsa verde onto the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish.Wrap the tortillas in a damp paper towel and microwave for one minute. Spoon a little of the chicken mixture down the center of each tortilla, tuck and roll, placing the tortilla, seam side down, into the baking dish.'),
(2111, 330, 13, 'Bake for 20 minutes or until the turnover cookies are golden brown. It may take longer than 20 minutes if your turnover cookies are particularly cold. Although you can eat them before they brown (you won\'t get sick), they are so much better when they have time to get a little crispy. You don\'t want them to burn, but they should achieve the golden brown color that you see in my photo.'),
(2112, 341, 5, 'Add sugar, peanut butter and whole milk. Beat an additional 3-5 minutes until fluffy. Fill a disposable pastry bag with frosting (no tip on end).Take a LARGE pastry bag and add both types of frosting, making sure the ends of each bag go down to the bottom. Using a 6S tip, pipe onto cupcakes. The peanut butter frosting is very light, so it\'s hard to see the swirl. That\'s okay, you will taste it!!'),
(2113, 336, 8, 'Pour the remaining salsa verde over top of the enchiladas and then top with the remaining the cheese.'),
(2114, 336, 9, 'Transfer to the oven and bake for 15-20 minutes, until the cheese has melted.'),
(2115, 336, 10, 'Remove and top with the Pineapple Avocado Salad.!Pineapple Avocado Salad'),
(2116, 336, 11, 'In a medium bowl, gently toss together all the ingredients. Keep stored in the fridge for up 2 days.'),
(2117, 343, 1, 'Pour steel cut oats into pot of boiling water. Simmer for about 25 minutes.'),
(2118, 343, 2, 'Mix in apple pie spice, butter and brown sugar, stirring gently to combine.Spoon into individual serving bowls and top with portion of chopped apple'),
(2119, 347, 1, 'Wet a piece of cheesecloth large enough to line the sieve or colander with a double layer and squeeze out the excess water.  Line the sieve or colander and set over a large bowl.  Set aside.Put milk, heavy cream, and salt in a large, heavy bottomed stock pot and bring to a rolling boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally to prevent scorching. Once the milk comes to a boil, add the lemon juice and stir constantly for two minutes, until the milk curdles.'),
(2120, 342, 1, 'Spread walnuts evenly in small baking dish or pie pan, and bake at 350F until fragrant and lightly browned, stirring twice, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
(2121, 347, 2, 'Pour the mixture into the lined sieve or colander and let it drain for an hour. Gently squeeze any excess whey out of the ricotta, store in an airtight container, and chill.'),
(2122, 344, 1, 'Add all of the ingredients to the bowl of a food processor and process in short bursts until finely ground.   Chill for 1 hour before serving.'),
(2123, 350, 1, 'Melt butter with mint leaves over medium heat in a small skillet or heavy-bottomed pot.Continue to heat the butter, stirring periodically, until it turns brown (10-15 minutes). The butter will first boil with big bubbles (it\'s not done then). Then, the bubbles will get smaller and the whole thing will look more brown (that\'s when it\'s done).'),
(2124, 350, 2, 'Remove butter from heat and strain the mint leaves out.  Press the butter out of the them as best you can.  Don\'t worry if you don\'t get it all - it\'s impossible  You only need 1/2 cup of the mint-flavored butter in the cookies.Cool the butter to room temperature - about thirty minutes.Preheat oven to 350 F.In a medium-sized mixing bowl, mix mint butter (there should be about 1/2 cup) and sugar until light and fluffy.'),
(2125, 350, 3, 'Mix in egg white and white chocolate.In a separate bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.'),
(2126, 350, 4, 'Add flour mixture to butter mixture a little bit at a time until just combined.'),
(2127, 349, 1, 'Mix all the ingredients except oil with a fork until smooth.'),
(2128, 350, 5, 'Place teaspoon-sized balls of dough about 1 1/2 inches apart on a parchment- or Silpat-lined cookie sheet.  The dough will be a little crumbly, so just push it together with your hands if you need to.'),
(2129, 349, 2, 'Heat a non stick pan and pour ½ tbsp oil in it. When the oil is very hot pour a ladle of batter on the same point in the pan and roll the panfrom side to side to give the batter a round shape.Cook it for 1 or 2 minutes. Just check the bottom with a wooden spatula when it releases and flip when it has the nice color you want. Flip it up and cook the other side for 1 or 2 minutes and transfer it on a plate.Repeat the same steps until you finish all the batter pouring ½ tbsp olive oil in the pan each time.'),
(2130, 345, 1, 'Butter a 9-inch deep-dish pie plate and dust with a tablespoon of sugar. Preheat the oven to 350F.Peel and slice the peaches. Toss with the raspberries. Set aside.Blend the sugar, milk, cream, eggs, vanilla, flour and salt in a blender for about a minute or until well blended.'),
(2131, 350, 6, 'Bake for 7-9 minutes or until the edges begin to brown.'),
(2132, 349, 3, 'Serve these right after you make with various fillings aside.'),
(2133, 345, 2, 'Pour half the custard mixture into the prepared pie plate. Arrange fruit on top and pour the remaining custard over the fruit.'),
(2134, 350, 7, 'Transfer to a cooling rack to cool.'),
(2135, 345, 3, 'Bake for 45-55 minutes, until the top is golden brown and puffy. Do not overcook. The custard should remain tender.'),
(2136, 345, 4, 'Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or creme anglaise.'),
(2137, 346, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.In large pot of boiling salted water, cook the macaroni to al dente (approximately 7 minutes). Strain and place on a lightly oiled sheet pan.While the macaroni is cooking, in a separate pot, melt 3 tablespoons of butter and whisk in the flour. Continue to cook over low heat for 4 minutes stirring constantly.'),
(2138, 346, 2, 'Add the milk, chopped truffles, onion and bay leaf. Simmer for 10 minutes.'),
(2139, 346, 3, 'Remove onion and bay leaf.Turn off the heat and add 3/4 of the aged cheddar and all of the other cheeses. Season with salt and black pepper and fold in macaroni.'),
(2140, 348, 1, 'In a large bowl, toss together salad ingredients.In a small bowl, whisk together cherry juice, balsamic vinegar, dijon and grainy mustard, garlic, and honey.Slowly whisk in the olive oil until throughly combined. '),
(2141, 346, 4, 'Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Top with remaining cheddar.Melt the remaining butter in a sauté pan and toss bread crumbs and parsley to coat. Top the macaroni with bread crumb mixture.'),
(2142, 348, 2, 'Add salt and pepper to taste.Toss the salad with as little or as much dressing as you like right before serving.'),
(2143, 346, 5, 'Bake for 30 minutes.'),
(2144, 346, 6, 'Remove from the oven let stand for about 5 minutes.'),
(2145, 346, 7, 'Serve with fresh shaved black truffles.'),
(2146, 352, 1, 'Preheat your oven to 400 degrees.In a saucepan on the stove, over low heat, melt the butter and saute the garlic for 1-2 minutes.'),
(2147, 352, 2, 'Add the tomato sauce.'),
(2148, 352, 3, 'Heat to boiling, then remove from heat.Stir to combine everything as much as possible.Rinse chicken and then pat dry with towel.'),
(2149, 352, 4, 'Place chicken in a square glass baking dish. Cover with the sauce and bake in oven at 400 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.While chicken is cooking, cook rice, pasta or quinoa and maybe grill up some veggies for a side dish.When chicken is done serve chicken and sauce over pasta, rice or quinoa.We topped ours with capers and some fresh purple basil and cilantro from our garden.'),
(2150, 353, 1, 'In a medium stainless steel saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Sweat onion until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes.'),
(2151, 353, 2, 'Add garlic and pepper, and cook for about 1 minute.'),
(2152, 359, 1, 'Scrub potatoes well to remove any dirt, then peel (unless you are using a food mill to process, in which case you do not need to peel your potatoes).'),
(2153, 353, 3, 'Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, and water; stir to combine. Reduce heat to medium-low and let simmer for approximately 15 minutes or until thickened slightly, stirring occasionally.'),
(2154, 355, 1, 'Light a grill over medium heat. In a medium bowl, combine ground turkey, red onions, jalapeos and Worcestershire sauce.'),
(2155, 358, 1, 'For the cookies:In a mixing bowl whisk together flour and salt. In the bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, cream together butter and sugar until well combined (scrape bowl occasionally throughout entire mixing process).'),
(2156, 359, 2, 'Cut potatoes into quarters or eighths, depending on the size. You want approximately 1-inch size pieces (all fairly even in size so they will cook uniformly) and transfer to a bowl filled with cold salted water. You can prep and cut your potatoes a few hours ahead of time if necessary; keep covered in water to prevent browning. Boil potatoes in a large pot of generously salted water for about 15 mintues minutes or until fork tender (a fork inserted into a piece of potato should go in easily and the potato should somewhat break apart).'),
(2157, 353, 4, 'Remove soup from heat.'),
(2158, 355, 2, 'Mix thoroughly. Divide the mixture into four equal portions. Form four patties with hands and place on the lighted grill. Cook for 5 minutes on each side or until desired level of done-ness is reached.'),
(2159, 354, 1, 'To create the batter, mix all ingredients, except fish, in a wide-bottomed bowl. The batter should be a consistency just slightly thicker than pancake batter.'),
(2160, 361, 1, 'Cook the pasta according to package directions.'),
(2161, 358, 2, 'Mix in egg yolks and vanilla extract then with mixer set on low speed, slowly add in flour mixture and mix just until combined. Scoop dough out 1 Tbsp at a time (24g) and shape into balls then place on a flat surface and make an indentation in middle of cookies with thumb.'),
(2162, 359, 3, 'Drain well. Run potatoes through a food mill placed on top of your still warm cooking pot on the still warm burner. The residual heat from the pot will evaporate out any excess moisture from the potatoes. If you don\'t have a food mill, run potatoes through a potato ricer, or place in the pot and mash with a potato masher until smooth.'),
(2163, 353, 5, 'Add the yogurt, the soup, cumin and salt to a blender. Blend until soup is smooth (To avoid spillage, make sure to press the lid of the blender on tightly).'),
(2164, 354, 2, 'Heat 2 Tbsp of oil in a large, non-stick frying pan until the oil pops when water is sprinkled on it.Dip your fish fillets into the batter, coating well on both sides. Gently lay fish in the hot oil (carefully, because it will splatter). Repeat with remaining fillets to fill the pan with just enough room so the pieces are not touching.Cook over medium high heat for 3-5 minutes. Flip the fish and cook for an additional 3-5 minutes on the other side, adding additional Tbsp of oil as needed.Fish is done when the filet feels firm and the outside is crisp.'),
(2165, 361, 2, 'Drain and reserve 1/4 cup of cooking liquid.'),
(2166, 358, 3, 'Transfer to plates (leaving a little space between cookies for even chilling. Also don\'t just make indentation when cookies are on plates or they\'ll likely stick) and chill in refrigerator 45 - 60 minutes. Preheat oven to 350 degrees halfway through chilling cookies.'),
(2167, 360, 1, 'To make sauce: In a small saucepan, combine the raspberries, sugar and lemon juice. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat, mashing the berries with a spoon.'),
(2168, 359, 4, 'Add butter and stir until melted, then add heavy cream and sesame oil. Season generously with salt and pepper.'),
(2169, 356, 1, 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
(2170, 353, 6, 'Pour in glass shots or bowls, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, and garnish with cilantro or parsley if desired. Spicy tomato soup can be accompanied by mini grilled cheese sandwiches. This recipe yields 5 (8-ounce) cups of soup.NOTE: To make Mini Grilled Cheese Sandwiches, sprinkle Kraft Grated Parmesan Cheese on the buttered sides of each sandwich and fill sandwich with a slice of your favorite semi-soft cheese (e.g. American cheese, Asadero, and the Brazilian Minas and Prato). Grill sandwiches in skillet until cheese melts and bread is toasty and golden brown. Slice into mini sandwiches (each standard-size sandwich can be sliced into thirds) and serve with spicy tomato soup shots.'),
(2171, 354, 3, 'Remove fish from pan to a plate lined with paper towels to soak up extra grease.Preheat oven to 450F.'),
(2172, 361, 3, 'Combine ricotta and next five ingredients (through pepper) and reserved cooking liquid in a large bowl.'),
(2173, 358, 4, 'Transfer cookies to a baking sheet lined with a silicone liner or parchment paper, spacing cookies 2-inches apart (keep remaining shaped cookies chilled).'),
(2174, 360, 2, 'Remove from heat and press through a fine-mesh sieve using the back of a spoon. Collect sauce in a bowl. Refrigerate until cold.For mousse: In a microwave safe bowl, combine white chocolate and  cup heavy cream. Microwave in 30 seconds intervals, stirring in between until chocolate is melted.In a large bowl, beat the rest of the heavy cream with a mixer on medium high speed until foamy.'),
(2175, 359, 5, 'Serve warm, topped with a sprinkle of toasted sesame seeds if desired.'),
(2176, 360, 3, 'Add in powdered sugar and vanilla extract. Beat until soft peaks form.'),
(2177, 358, 5, 'Bake in preheated oven 14 - 15 minutes until set.'),
(2178, 357, 1, 'First up, prep your kale by washing it well and cutting it off of the stem.The massage the kale leaves in a large bowl with a drizzle of olive oil, half of the lemon juice and a pinch of kosher salt. This is the secret to tasty raw kale! The prep the red onions and red pepper.Meanwhile, make the dressing!'),
(2179, 354, 4, 'Place cut potatoes in a large bowl, spray lightly with cooking spray and toss to coat.Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Grease the foil with cooking spray and place potatoes on foil. Sprinkle with salt or seasoned salt to taste.'),
(2180, 361, 4, 'Add the pasta and toss to combine.'),
(2181, 356, 2, 'In a large bowl, toss the apples with the sugar, lemon zest and juice, rum (if using), vanilla, cornstarch, nutmeg and salt. Macerate at room temperature for about 2 hours or, refrigerated, overnight.'),
(2182, 360, 4, 'Remove about a cup (eye-ball it) of the whipped cream mixture and whisk into the melted chocolate. Fold in the rest of the whipped cream into the chocolate until combined.Divide half of the mousse among 6 small glasses or ramekins. Top with each with a tablespoon of raspberry sauce and a few raspberries. Top with remaining mousse, sauce and raspberries. Sprinkle with shaved white chocolate. Refrigerate until cold, at least 30 minutes before serving.'),
(2183, 357, 2, 'Whisk together tahini, extra virgin olive oil, vinegar, water, lemon juice, smoked paprika, and salt and pepper to taste.Now add the red onions and red peppers to the kale and dress with the tahini dressing and sesame seeds.Toss and garnish with avocado, goat cheese and sunflower seeds.'),
(2184, 354, 5, 'Bake potatoes for 15 min.'),
(2185, 361, 5, 'Garnish with lemon wedges if desired and serve immediately.'),
(2186, 356, 3, 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.'),
(2187, 354, 6, 'Remove from oven and turn the chips with a spatula. Return to oven to bake an additional 10 – 15 min. Chips are done when crisp and golden.'),
(2188, 361, 6, 'Serves 6-8.'),
(2189, 356, 4, 'Dust a worktop and rolling pin with flour.'),
(2190, 356, 5, 'Roll out one dough disk a little less than 1/4-inch thick, about 14 inches in diameter. Fold the dough in half and transfer it to a 9- or 10-inch pie plate. Unfold. Press the dough into the corners, leaving the overhang. Refrigerate the first crust while you roll out the second disk of dough.'),
(2191, 356, 6, 'Remove the bottom crust from the fridge and fill it with the macerated apples. Tuck the pats of cold butter beneath the top layer of fruit. Top with the second piece of dough, and trim both to a 1/2-inch overhang. Tuck the overhang into a roll and crimp the edge, pressing down to hook some of the dough over the edge of the dish. (You want to make a hard crimp because it will shrink as it cooks.)'),
(2192, 356, 7, 'Cut a hole in the center of the pie, as well as some decorative vents.'),
(2193, 356, 8, 'Brush the top of the pie with cream, dust it with sugar, and bake for 20 minutes.'),
(2194, 356, 9, 'Then reduce the temperature to 350 degrees F and bake for another 45 to 55 minutes, until the center juices bubble and thicken, for a total of about 1 hour 10 minutes.'),
(2195, 362, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees (F). Cook pasta according to package directions. Do not overcook!'),
(2196, 356, 10, 'Let the pie cool until it is just warm to the touch before slicing and serving.'),
(2197, 362, 2, 'Drain and set aside.Salt and pepper both sides of the pieces of chicken. Dredge chicken in flour.'),
(2198, 356, 11, 'Mix the flour, sugar, and salt in a large bowl.'),
(2199, 362, 3, 'Heat olive oil and butter in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven on the stovetop over medium-high heat.'),
(2200, 356, 12, 'Add the lard and the butter, and cut them in with a pastry blender until the larger pieces are the size of peas and the mixture begins to clump on the pastry blender. Shuffle through the mixture with your hands, pinching chunks of lard to flatten them.'),
(2201, 362, 4, 'Place chicken skin down in pan, four pieces at a time. Brown chicken on both sides, then remove to a clean plate. Repeat with remaining chicken.'),
(2202, 356, 13, 'Add 4 tablespoons of the ice water and mix with a fork. Pinch a clump of dough in your hands: If it feels moist and clumps together easily, it\'s probably hydrated enough. If it feels really crumbly, add another tablespoon or two of ice water until you can form a baseball-size clump of dough, packing it on as if you were making a snowball. You want to mix the dough as little as possible to ensure it stays tender.'),
(2203, 362, 5, 'Pour off half the fat in the pan and discard.'),
(2204, 356, 14, 'Divide the dough in half and form each half into a flat disk. Wrap both disks in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour and up to 2 days.'),
(2205, 362, 6, 'Add sliced onions and peppers, as well as the garlic. Stir around for 1 minute.'),
(2206, 356, 15, 'Thirty minutes before you\'re ready to roll out the dough, remove it from the refrigerator and let it sit at room temperature to soften.'),
(2207, 362, 7, 'Add mushrooms and stir around for 1 minute.'),
(2208, 362, 8, 'Add thyme, turmeric, and salt. (And crushed red pepper flakes if you like things a little spicy.)'),
(2209, 362, 9, 'Add extra black pepper to taste. Stir, then pour in wine. Allow to bubble.'),
(2210, 362, 10, 'Pour in canned tomatoes and stir to combine.'),
(2211, 362, 11, 'Add chicken back into the pan, skin side up, without totally submerging the chicken.'),
(2212, 362, 12, 'Place lid on the pot and put it into the oven for 45 minutes.'),
(2213, 362, 13, 'Remove lid and increase heat to 375 degrees. Cook for an additional 15 minutes.'),
(2214, 362, 14, 'Remove pan from the oven.'),
(2215, 362, 15, 'Remove chicken from the pot and place it on a plate.'),
(2216, 363, 1, 'Preheat grill to medium heat (about 300 degrees).Grill hot dogs over medium heat for about 2 minutes. Flip the hot dogs and cook on the other side for another 2 minutes, or until they are heated through and have nice grill marks.'),
(2217, 363, 2, 'Remove from grill.'),
(2218, 363, 3, 'Place one hot dog in each bun.'),
(2219, 369, 1, 'Ideal Slow Cooker: 1 to 2-Quart.Fully drain the can of corn and discard the liquid.Partially drain the can of tomatoes, leaving about half the liquid.'),
(2220, 369, 2, 'Pour the corn and tomatoes with their remaining liquid into the slow cooker.'),
(2221, 363, 4, 'Spread 1 tablespoon of guacamole along one side of the hot dog and 1 tablespoon of salsa along the other. Top with crumbled queso fresco and sliced jalapeños.'),
(2222, 362, 16, 'Remove vegetables from pot and place them on a plate. Return pot to burner and turn heat to medium high. Cook and reduce sauce for a couple of minutes.'),
(2223, 363, 5, 'Serve warm with chips, salsa and guacamole.'),
(2224, 362, 17, 'Pour cooked, drained noodles on a large platter or in a big serving bowl.'),
(2225, 366, 1, '1'),
(2226, 369, 3, 'Add the cubes of cream cheese.Cover and cook on LOW for one to 2 hours, stirring occasionally, until cream cheese is melted and dip is warmed through.'),
(2227, 362, 18, 'Add vegetables all over the top, then place chicken pieces on top of the vegetables. Spoon juices from the pot over the chicken and pasta (amount to taste.)Before serving, sprinkle on chopped fresh parsley and grated Parmesan.'),
(2228, 366, 2, 'Heat oven to 375°F. In large bowl, stir milk and peanut butter until smooth. Stir in Bisquick mix and vanilla.'),
(2229, 369, 4, 'Serve warm with your favorite veggies and corn chips for dipping.Makes about 2-1/2 cups'),
(2230, 366, 3, '2'),
