(2235, 371, 3, 'Spread into a 9x13\" pan lined with tin foil. Set in the freezer to firm up while you melt the chocolate.'),
(2236, 366, 5, 'Roll tops in sugar.'),
(2237, 368, 2, 'Add beef, a few pieces at a time, and shake to coat.'),
(2238, 366, 6, 'Place sugar side up 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.'),
(2239, 367, 1, 'In a large bowl, cream butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.'),
(2240, 371, 4, 'Combine chocolate chips and milk and microwave on high in 30-45 second intervals, stirring each time, just until the chocolate is melted (don\'t overdue it!). I did 45 seconds, 30 seconds, 20 seconds and it was perfect.'),
(2241, 368, 3, 'Remove meat form bag; pound to flatten.'),
(2242, 368, 4, 'In a large skillet over medium-high heat, brown steak on both sides in butter.'),
(2243, 371, 5, 'Spread evenly over bars and refrigerate until firm (you can put them in the freezer if you\'re in a hurry!). Slice into bars and serve. I recommend storing in the fridge or freezer.'),
