(4788, 811, 3, 'Add wine to the bottom of the pan. (I like to place the neck in the bottom of the roasting pan as well to let it roast and enhance the cooking juices that I make gravy out of  completely optional).  Insert a cooking thermometer into a turkey thigh. Roast for 1 hour and 45 minutes.While the turkey is roasting, combine orange juice, brown sugar, and sage leaves in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a rapid simmer (medium-low) and simmer until reduced to 1/3 cup and slightly thickened. After the turkey has roasted for 1 hour 45 minutes, brush the glaze over the turkey.Return to the oven and continue to cook for 20 minutes or until the thermometer reads 170F. (Total roasting time should be between 2 and 2 1/2 hours).'),
(4789, 811, 4, 'Transfer turkey to a cutting board and allow to rest 10 to 20 minutes before carving. To Make Gravy: While the turkey is resting you can make gravy out of the juices by bringing the cooking juices to a simmer in the roasting pan or a saucepan.'),
