(5202, 882, 5, 'Light one chimney full of charcoal. When all the charcoal is lit and covered with gray ash, pour out and spread the coals evenly over the coal grate. Set cooking grate in place, cover grill and allow to preheat for 5 minutes. Alternatively, preheat a gas grill to high, covered, for at least 10 minutes. Clean and oil the grilling grate.'),
(5203, 883, 2, 'Combine all ingredients, using your hands. Divide the meat into 6 equal portions. With each portion divide it again in half when forming the burgers. Flatten out one half, place a slice of fresh mozzarella on top and top with remaining half of meat, forming into a round flat patty, pinching the sides closed, so the cheese isn\'t exposed.Repeat with all the meat, making 6 burgers.'),
