(5224, 877, 2, 'Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or split.In a bowl of an electric mixer cream together butter and brown sugar.Once creamed together add egg, and vanilla extract and beat until incorporated.In a small bowl whisk together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg.With the electric mixer on low, slowly pour the flour mix into the butter mixture. Blend until combined.'),
(5225, 883, 5, 'Place bread on a baking sheet and place under the broiler, or on the grill for 1-2 minutes until toasted. (If you use the broiler watch closely so bread doesn\'t burn!)As soon as the bread is toasted, remove it from the broiler or grill and rub with the inside of remaining clove of garlic that has been halved.When burgers are done, place on non-toasted side of bread, top with a generous portion of Bruschetta and the other slice of toast.'),
