(5325, 896, 1, 'Preheat oven to 400° F.In a small bowl, combine 3 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon. Set aside.In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.In a large bowl, mix the 1 cup sugar, butter, shortening, and eggs.  Beat in the dry ingredients. Fold in the toffee bits.Scoop dough into 1 1/4-inch rounded balls; roll in the sugar/cinnamon mixture.'),
